Alpha: The Deep Relaxation Waves

Alpha brainwaves are present during deep relaxation and light meditation. Alpha is ‘the power of now', the being 'here' in the present. Alpha is the resting state for the brain, and these waves aid overall mental coordination, calmness, concentration, memory and learning.

contents.name: Adrift Theta

Do not listen while driving or operating machinery. Use headphones to get the full benefits of the brainwave entrainment audio technology and do not listen at a loud volume.

Light and relaxing music with Theta Waves.  

Theta: The Light Sleep and Deep Meditation Waves 

Theta brainwaves occur most often in sleep, (including the REM dream state) but also during deep meditation. Theta is that short transition state which we normally only experience while drifting off to sleep or when emerging from a deep sleep. In this state, we are aware of our surroundings, but the body is completely relaxed. Theta is the source of vivid dreams, intuition, creativity, memory, and learning.

Delta brainwaves are generated in deep, dreamless sleep, as well as in very deep meditation usually only achieved by experienced meditators. In this state, you are completely unconscious of your surroundings and your body is inert. Here, healing and regeneration are stimulated, which is why deep restorative sleep is so essential to our lives & healing processes.

contents.name: Breathe. Repeat!
contents.title: Breathe. Repeat!
contents.description:
Learning to notice your breath is a simple practice and a great step toward putting your meditation practice in motion.

Whenever you can, try to remember to take a conscious breath or two - breaths you follow fully with your complete attention.

Use everyday triggers to remind you, like stop signs or your phone buzzing.

Notice how focusing on your breath takes you out of thinking and into the present moment.

contents.name: Oh my Aching Back!
contents.title: Oh my Aching Back!
contents.description:
How we feel physically is often a direct result of how we feel mentally.

Becoming more aware of this connection is an important step.

Be attentive to those stress-related sensations, like tightness in your stomach, teeth clenching, headaches etc.

Rather than trying to ignore the sensation, or make it go away, just breathe into it.

Take time to consider how the feeling might be connected to your mental state. 

Then just let it go.

contents.name: One Minute Meditation
contents.title: One Minute Meditation
contents.description:
Many people think meditation takes a lot of time and has to be done in a perfectly quite place.  

But, you can meditate anywhere you like, for as short a time as you like, even when it's noisy.  

Try the "One Minute Meditation" which you can find in the 'Life Situations - Pressed for Time' section of the app.  

Learn it by heart and make it your go-to tool whenever you need a quick shot of calm and clarity.

contents.name: Turn Off Auto-Pilot
contents.title: Turn Off Auto-Pilot
contents.description:
Ever notice how your mind tends to wander when you’re doing those habitual things, like brushing your teeth, or taking a shower, or even walking down the street.  

The more automatic things are, the more our minds run wild.

These are great opportunities to be mindful and become aware of our senses.

Notice the taste of the toothpaste, the feeling of the water on your body, or the sights and sounds as you walk.

contents.name: Wherever You Go, There You Are
contents.title: Wherever You Go, There You Are
contents.description:
Certain books can be wonderful companions to your meditation practice.  

Jon Kabat-Zinn’s best-seller "Wherever You Go, There You Are" is one of the most readable and understandable books on how to bring mindfulness into your life.

Pick up the book and keep it by your bedside.  

Read it all at once, or a few pages a day.  

Think of it as a protein shot for your attention muscle!
contents.short_title: Wherever You Go, There You Are

contents.name: Are You Where Your Body Is?
contents.title: Are You Where Your Body Is?
contents.description:
Most of us spend a lot of time worrying about the future, or thinking about the past.

Each moment that we're not in the Here & Now, is a moment not fully lived.

As often as possible, ask yourself the question: Am I where my body is?

If you find your mind in a different time or place, simply bring yourself back into the present moment by focusing on your breath, the sounds around you, or feelings in your body.
contents.short_title: Are You Where Your Body Is?

contents.name: Call Me Baby!
contents.title: Call Me Baby!
contents.description:
A newborn baby is fully present and experiences life only through only its five senses. 

It has no story and no history and, therefore, no stress or anxiety.

Sure, it has physical needs, but as soon as they're met, they're let go.

Notice how much of your stress is created by the storyline created in your mind.

contents.name: Me, Myself and I
contents.title: Me, Myself and I
contents.description:
Most of us identify very strongly with our feelings.  

We say things like like "I'm angry", "My sadness" or "I'm afraid." 

But it's possible to step back and allow feelings to simply be, without identifying with them.

Observe these feelings with a bit of detachment, just as you do with your thoughts in meditation.  

You'll soon begin to experience these feelings without having them pull you into a downward spiral.

contents.name: Nothing More Than Feelings
contents.title: Nothing More Than Feelings
contents.description:
Ever notice how some emotions are much stronger than others.  

Investigating these powerful feelings is a great practice.

Whenever you feel strong emotions arising – such as anger or fear – trace them back to their root.  

Find the thoughts that are behind them, ask yourself why your feelings are so strong.

Your strongest emotions are always about you at the end of the day, even when they seem to be directed at others.

contents.name: And … Cut!
contents.title: And … Cut!
contents.description:
If we look at our lives as a movie, we always have the choice of playing the "Diva" or being the "Cameraman."

As the Diva, we're wrapped up in the drama of our movie, but as the Cameraman, we watch the drama without getting caught up in it.

The Cameraman's perspective is the peaceful place we cultivate in meditation.

Notice those moments that pull you into the drama, and see if you can step back and become the Cameraman instead.

contents.name: Nothing's Happening
contents.title: Nothing's Happening
contents.description:
Often, when we first begin meditating, we don't notice the small changes that are taking place in us.  

Usually, it's about what's happening less in our lives, like anger or conflict, or just less stress and anxiety. 

Often, it's the people around us that notice that we seem happier or calmer, before we notice it ourselves.

Look carefully for those small signs of change, like how you're relating to those around you or how your body feels.

contents.name: Human Being vs. Human Doing
contents.title: Human Being vs. Human Doing
contents.description:
In meditation, we practice finding that balance between effort and relaxation.

But in our daily lives, we often find ourselves striving diligently and effortfully for what we want.

Take time to notice when you find yourself working a bit too hard to make things happen.
  
See what happens when you take a breath, let go a bit, and allow life to unfold on its own.

contents.name: Shake off the Should's
contents.title: Shake off the Should's
contents.description:
Many of us spend a lot of time and energy trying to satisfy other people's expectations of us, rather than our own. 

When we tell ourselves we "should" do something, it's a good clue that it may not be our own authentic voice speaking.  

It's often someone else's voice that we're hearing.  

So take time to consider your motivation for doing those things you think you "should" be doing.

If it's your own voice, that's great. 

But if not, who's is it?

contents.name: Weather or Not!
contents.title: Weather or Not!
contents.description:
Each day, Mother Nature decides what type of weather we'll be presented with.

Calm sunny days… Stormy days…

How we react to the weather gives us a sense of how we tend to react to our ever-changing life circumstances.

Notice if you tend to judge certain weather as good or bad. 

Consider how this tendency to judge may apply to other areas of your life, and remember that even the worst weather is only temporary.

contents.name: What to Expect When You're Expecting
contents.title: What to Expect When You're Expecting
contents.description:
Did you know that much of our stress comes from things being different than how we want them to be?

How we react when life throws us curve balls can determine our happiness.

Take time to notice how you react when things just don't go your way.  

Even small things like sitting in traffic, getting caught in the rain, or too much foam in your latte…

Take a breath and see if you can let it go.
contents.short_title: What to Expect When You're Expecting

contents.name: The Attitude of Gratitude
contents.title: The Attitude of Gratitude
contents.description:
For many of us, the word gratitude implies a Thanksgiving speech, which is standing in the way of a big meal.

But living with gratitude has been proven to bring increased happiness. 

By focusing on what's good in your life, rather than what's missing, your mindset shifts from lack to abundance.  

This simple shift in focus from glass half empty to half full changes how you see the world.

Try it out and notice how your spirit lifts.

contents.name: Kitchen Consequential
contents.title: Kitchen Consequential
contents.description:
Cooking is really a great way to practice being fully present, and it can be a wonderful way to experience all of your senses in one activity.

Prepare and enjoy a meal using all five of your senses.  

Savor the aromas, visually delight in the colors, listen to the sounds, and feel the textures as you prepare your meal.

And when you're done, enjoy the taste of your creation as you eat it mindfully.

contents.name: Don't Take it Personally
contents.title: Don't Take it Personally
contents.description:
Have you noticed how we often assume things are about us when, in fact, they have nothing to do with us.  

These assumptions are just our personal stories.

Notice how often you assume things are about you when there's no evidence to back it up. 

If someone ignores you, and you take it personally, you may think "What did I do to deserve that?". 

But if you take yourself out of the equation, you might realize they're just simply distracted.

contents.name: The In-Betweens
contents.title: The In-Betweens
contents.description:
Just as we look at silence as simply the space between sounds, we look at the time between activities as a sort of 'nothingness' as well. 

We may call it "waiting," or "boredom," but what we're really saying is this time doesn't really count.  

Whether it's traffic delays, waiting in lines, or just plain nothing to do time, give these moments equal respect.  

Give these 'in between' times your full presence.

contents.name: You Take My Breath Away
contents.title: You Take My Breath Away
contents.description:
Most of us get so caught up in our lives that we forget about our own breathing.

When we get anxious, we often have a tendency to breathe very shallowly, or even hold our breath.

Bring more awareness to your breathing.  

As often as you can, notice the simple fact that you are breathing.
  
Talking to people is a great place to practice this. See if you can keep a bit of your attention on your breath as you listen to people speak.

contents.name: The Power of Now
contents.title: The Power of Now
contents.description:
Spiritual Master, Eckhart Tolle's classic book "The Power of Now", has opened the door for millions of people to the transformative power and simplicity of being in the present moment.

Get yourself a copy of "The Power of Now" and give it a read. 

If you're like many others, you may discover that living in the now is the simplest path to happiness and fulfillment.

contents.name: Sounds of Silence
contents.title: Sounds of Silence
contents.description:
We often overlook silence as simply the space between sounds.  

But silence has a quality of its own, and learning to pay attention to it helps us tune in to the present moment.

Try to give silence the same attention you give sounds.  

Notice the gaps between words and sounds, and maybe even the underlying silence behind all sounds. 

Observe how connecting to silence can instantly fill you with a sense of peace.

contents.name: The Power of Intention
contents.title: The Power of Intention
contents.description:
Intention is the starting point of every dream. 

It is the spark that ignites the creative power that fulfills our desires – whether for love, money, spiritual awakening, or whatever else we seek. 

Your mission is to start each day by setting an intention. It can be a long-term goal in your life, a new way of being, or simply something you'd like to make happen in the day ahead.

Trust in the power of intention.

contents.name: Sweet Dreams
contents.title: Sweet Dreams
contents.description: Having a restful sleep with peaceful dreams is something we all want when we turn in for the evening. This relaxing meditation will help you unwind and drift off to sleep with peaceful and soothing visualizations.

contents.name: Countdown
contents.title: Countdown
contents.description: Use this meditation to help your mind switch off from the thoughts of your day and slowly countdown into a peaceful and relaxing sleep.

contents.name: Meditation for Insomnia
contents.title: Meditation for Insomnia
contents.description: Use this guided visualization to help you relax your body and mind as you fall asleep.

contents.name: Body Relaxation
contents.title: Body Relaxation
contents.description: Relax your whole body with this meditation designed to help you release all the stress and tension stored in your body. It will leave you feeling calm, peaceful and completely relaxed, as you drift off to sleep.

contents.name: Deep Sleep - Long Version
contents.title: Deep Sleep - Long Version
contents.description:
Trouble sleeping? Use this visualization to help you find the sleep you need by calming your mind and connecting with a feeling of presence and peace.

Introduction music written by Glenn Harrold Individual background music pieces by Glenn Harrold and Christopher Lloyd Clarke.

contents.name: Deep Sleep - Short Version
contents.title: Deep Sleep - Short Version
contents.description:
Switch off and fall into a deep and peaceful sleep. This visualization is designed to help you still your mind and clear away any worries and anxieties so you can drift away.

Introduction music written by Glenn Harrold Individual background music pieces by Glenn Harrold and Christopher Lloyd Clarke.

contents.name: Peaceful Forest
contents.title: Peaceful Forest
contents.description: This visualisation guides you on a journey through a peaceful and tranquil forest environment, encouraging a state of complete relaxation.

contents.name: Relaxing on the Beach
contents.title: Relaxing on the Beach
contents.description: Allow yourself to experience complete relaxation, as you are transported to a tranquil and relaxing beach environment, where you can submerse yourself in the clear calm waters and let all your tension dissolve.

contents.name: Floating on a Cloud
contents.title: Floating on a Cloud
contents.description: Let your whole body unwind and relax as you float away on a cloud in this peaceful guided visualization.

contents.name: Peaceful Meadow
contents.title: Peaceful Meadow
contents.description: Let this relaxing visualization ease away all the tension from your body and mind, leaving you feeling completely relaxed, as you take an imaginary journey through a beautiful and peaceful meadow.

contents.name: Legs Up Before Bed Meditation
contents.title: Legs Up Before Bed Meditation
contents.description: This guided meditation works as a natural sleep aid if you're struggling with insomnia.

contents.name: Transition to Sleep
contents.title: Transition to Sleep
contents.description: Calm anxiety or stress and relax your mind so you can drift into a peaceful and restful sleep.

contents.name: Bedtime Body Scan
contents.title: Bedtime Body Scan
contents.description: Allow sleep to come and gently take you away as you relax your entire body from head to toe.

contents.name: Just Before Bed
contents.title: Just Before Bed
contents.description: Come let go of the busyness of your day and prepare yourself for a deep and restful sleep.

contents.name: Drift Into Sleep
contents.title: Drift Into Sleep
contents.description: Having trouble sleeping? Settle in and get comfortable and let this meditation take you on a peaceful journey to deep and restful sleep.

contents.name: Sleep Lullabye at the Sea
contents.title: Sleep Lullabye at the Sea
contents.description: Let the soothing spoken lullaby and sounds of the sea support you to fall deeply asleep.

contents.name: Attracting Abundance
contents.title: Attracting Abundance
contents.description: Abundance is something we all want a bit more of in our lives. Not just material abundance, but abundance of love, peace, and happiness. It all starts with your mindset. This meditation will help you grow the feelings of abundance that come from within.

contents.name: Finding Love
contents.title: Finding Love
contents.description: Love is something we all want a bit more of in our lives. Not just someone to love us, but the ability to give love and live our lives with a sense of love. It all starts with your mindset. This meditation will help you develop a sense of love within you, that can then find its way into your life

contents.name: The Butterfly
contents.title: The Butterfly
contents.description: This is a playful visualization to help your child focus and relax each body part, one at a time, leaving them feeling peaceful, calm and relaxed.

contents.name: Releasing Fear
contents.title: Releasing Fear
contents.description: We all have fears. But how we deal with our fear is up to us. Fear can be healthy, and can help us react quickly to avoid imminent physical danger. But much of our fear is psychological, such as worrying about something in the future that may or may not happen. This type of fear is created in your mind. This meditation will help you become more aware of how your fears can get in the way of happiness, and help you release them.

contents.name: Dealing with Anxiety
contents.title: Dealing with Anxiety
contents.description: Anxiety comes from our minds being in the future, and not in the present moment. This guided visualization will take you on a journey away from your worrisome thoughts.

contents.name: Developing Patience
contents.title: Developing Patience
contents.description: When you’re feeling impatient, you’re trying to get to the future faster than the speed of life.

contents.name: Better Conflict Resolution
contents.title: Better Conflict Resolution
contents.description: This meditation will help you find more authentic communication and heart-felt resolution of conflict in your relationships.

contents.name: Managing Reactivity
contents.title: Managing Reactivity
contents.description: We are all confronted regularly with situations that cause us to react automatically, and without thinking. This meditation will help bring awareness to those situations, and help you deal with life in a more grounded and centered way.

contents.name: The Mindful Moment Meditation
contents.title: The Mindful Moment Meditation
contents.description: Practice one minute of mindfulness anywhere you are, and as often as you like during the day, to bring you back to the present moment. It only takes one minute and you can do it with your eyes open.

contents.name: Two Minute Stress Reliever
contents.title: Two Minute Stress Reliever
contents.description: Feeling anxious but only have two minutes? Use this short meditation to take the opportunity to de-stress and relax. Your body and mind will thank you.

contents.name: Healing
contents.title: Healing
contents.description: The hidden cause of physical illness can sometimes be negative blockages in your energy field. Let this recording guide you to gently reduce or even remove any discomfort and focus your energy on clearing these blocks.

contents.name: Five Minute Meditation
contents.title: Five Minute Meditation
contents.description: Use this short meditation to give you that break you need in your busy day. You’ll be amazed at how refreshed you will feel after just 5 minutes.

contents.name: Self Healing
contents.title: Self Healing
contents.description: The physical sensations of pain and discomfort are often unpleasant, but it is the constant struggle in the mind that can magnify health issues. This recording will help you to reduce or even remove any discomfort and help you heal your mind and body.

contents.name: Waiting in Lines
contents.title: Waiting in Lines
contents.description: Use the time you spend waiting in lines to help you develop patience, self-awareness and a sense of gratitude for how precious each and every moment is.

contents.name: Public Places (Eyes Open)
contents.title: Public Places (Eyes Open)
contents.description: The daily commute is a great time to practice your meditation skills. Enjoy this guided mindfulness practice with your eyes open. No one will even know you're meditating!

contents.name: Mindful Eating
contents.title: Mindful Eating
contents.description: Practicing mindful eating is an important way of not only improving your digestive process, but also a way to practice being in the moment and appreciating what a gift each meal we have really is.

contents.name: Mindful Walking
contents.title: Mindful Walking
contents.description: Use this meditation to become more aware of your body, mind and environment as you walk. Practicing mindful walking helps you cultivate mindfulness into all areas of your life.

contents.name: Releasing Anxiety - Short Version
contents.title: Releasing Anxiety - Short Version
contents.description: Whenever you feel worried, anxious or stressed you can learn to notice your thoughts as they come and go. Use this recording to help you develop this skill and release yourself from the cycle of anxiety and worry.

contents.name: Releasing Anxiety
contents.title: Releasing Anxiety
contents.description: This recording will help you reduce your anxiety by learning how to anchor yourself in the present moment. Here you will be less likely to get caught up in worries about the future or regrets over the past.

contents.name: Visualizing Gratitude
contents.title: Visualizing Gratitude
contents.description: Grateful people are happy people. Use this bedtime visualization to help you cultivate a sense of appreciation and gratitude in your life.

contents.name: Letting Go of Control
contents.title: Letting Go of Control
contents.description: Sometimes in life we feel a need to control things in order to feel safe and secure. However, this need to control can actually prevent us from experiencing life to the fullest. Use this guided visualization to help you let go and open yourself to all of the possibilities life has to offer.

contents.name: Finding Inner Peace
contents.title: Finding Inner Peace
contents.description: Inner peace resides within us and is always there for us to tap into. This meditation will help you access that reservoir of peace.

contents.name: Overcoming Negativity
contents.title: Overcoming Negativity
contents.description: Our thoughts create our reality. The more we can replace negative thoughts with a more positive outlook, the more our lives will follow suit. This meditation will help you become more aware of your negative patterns of thinking and help you overcome them.

contents.name: Positive Self-Image
contents.title: Positive Self-Image
contents.description: Maintaining a positive self-image can sometimes be difficult, especially if your life has been affected by personal hardships, difficult relationships, or other problems. But only you are ultimately in control of how you perceive yourself. This meditation will help you become more aware of how your own thoughts create your self-image, and to help you replace old negative thinking patterns with ones of self-worth and positive image.

contents.name: Overcoming Insecurity
contents.title: Overcoming Insecurity
contents.description: We all feel insecure at times. Even people who are generally quite confident can find themselves in situations that make them feel insecure. Feelings of insecurity tend to arise when we view ourselves through other people’s eyes, when our own self-image doesn’t match how we want to be seen. This guided visualization will help you bring awareness to these feelings.

contents.name: Becoming More Playful
contents.title: Becoming More Playful
contents.description: Playfulness is an important part of life. It helps us to enjoy ourselves and to cope with certain situations in a more light-hearted way. This guided meditation will help you reconnect with your own inner child and and let it express itself in your everyday life.

contents.name: Sport Performance
contents.title: Sport Performance
contents.description: In order to perform at your best athletically, your mind needs to be focused and clear. Use this guided meditation to create clarity and confidence by visualizing the results you are looking for.

contents.name: Meditation for Success
contents.title: Meditation for Success
contents.description: We all strive for success in our lives, but it has a different meaning for each of us. Whether it’s financial success, relationship success, or just the achievement of the personal goals we set for ourselves. Use this guided visualization to help you connect with the strength, determination and drive that is within you, and to help push you toward the achievement of your goals.

contents.name: Overcoming Obstacles
contents.title: Overcoming Obstacles
contents.description: We all face challenges on the path toward the goals we set for ourselves. But we can choose whether we view these challenges as insurmountable obstacles, or simply stepping stones on our way to the achievement of the goal. This guided visualization will help you re-frame the way you look at obstacles.

contents.name: Blood Pressure
contents.title: Blood Pressure
contents.description: For when you're feeling stressed and tense and your blood pressure is on the rise. Use this meditation to relax and calm yourself from head to toe.

contents.name: Sexual Energy
contents.title: Sexual Energy
contents.description: As adults, our sexuality is an integral part of who we are. This guided meditation will help you awaken and connect with your sexual energies, and balance them and guide them in positive directions, allowing you to be more confident and comfortable with your sexual nature.

contents.name: Managing Pain
contents.title: Managing Pain
contents.description: We all experience pain at times in our lives, and it can be very debilitating and difficult to cope with. This guided visualization will help soothe and relax your body and your mind, and enable you to manage and reduce suffering from pain.

contents.name: Headaches
contents.title: Headaches
contents.description: Headaches and migraines can be incredibly painful and debilitating, and often feel like they are lasting forever. This guided meditation will walk you through a series of soothing and relaxing visualizations that will help you ease the source of your discomfort.

contents.name: Guided Body Scan
contents.title: Guided Body Scan
contents.description: The guided body scan meditation develops your ability to intentionally move attention around. It also teaches you to focus deeply on different regions of your body, and notice how each part feels, without trying to change anything. You learn to just be with what is there. As time goes by, you will find that you become more at ease, and less absorbed by your thoughts and feelings.

contents.name: Fear of Flying
contents.title: Fear of Flying
contents.description: Use this meditation to enjoy a peaceful flight instead of one full of worry and stress.

contents.name: Overcoming Shyness
contents.title: Overcoming Shyness
contents.description: Shyness is something many of us experience from time to time when we find ourselves in social situations that we are not fully comfortable in. This guided visualization will bring awareness to how our shyness comes from anxiety that can arise in these situations, and will open up the possibility of dealing with this anxiety in new ways that serve us better.

contents.name: Dealing with Loneliness
contents.title: Dealing with Loneliness
contents.description: Loneliness is often thought of as simply not having enough people in your life. But many people are actually very happy being alone. The root of the feeling of loneliness arises from within, from a sense of disconnectedness with our higher self. This guided visualization will help you get in touch with feelings of loneliness at their root, and allow you to connect with the inner sense of self that is always with you.

contents.name: Fear of Darkness
contents.title: Fear of Darkness
contents.description: This guided visualization will help deal with the fear of darkness. You may wish to do this meditation in a dark place, provided you can assure yourself that the place is truly safe. Take the time you need before starting this meditation to check whatever you need to, to feel as much at ease as possible.

contents.name: Stop Procrastinating
contents.title: Stop Procrastinating
contents.description: There are many reasons people tend to procrastinate. Fear… Laziness… Lack of motivation... This meditation will help you bring these reasons to your awareness and help you get past them.

contents.name: Building Self-Esteem
contents.title: Building Self-Esteem
contents.description: We all have feelings of self-doubt from time to time. This visualization will help you become more aware that these thoughts and feelings don’t define you, and to realize that you are exactly as you are meant to be.

contents.name: Authentic Self
contents.title: Authentic Self
contents.description: For many of us, the pressures of daily life, and living up to the expectations of others, can cause us to lose sight of what we truly need and value for ourselves. This guided meditation will help you re-connect with the values and feelings of your authentic self.

contents.name: Flexibilty & Resilience
contents.title: Flexibilty & Resilience
contents.description: We all face obstacles in our lives. In order to move past them, we need to be both flexible, and resilient. This guided visualization will help you access your own storehouse of inner strength and creativity to help you deal with the challenges in your life.

contents.name: Managing your Anger
contents.title: Managing your Anger
contents.description: We all get angry from time to time. But how we deal with our anger can have a big effect on our state of mind and our actual health. It’s been said that holding on to anger is like grasping a hot coal with the intention of throwing it at someone. In the end, you’re the one that gets burned.

contents.name: Panic Attacks
contents.title: Panic Attacks
contents.description: Panic attacks are something that many people experience. They can be very uncomfortable and quite scary. This guided visualization is designed to bring awareness to the causes of panic attacks and to help ease their discomfort as they happen through a focus on the breath. It’s very important to be able to distinguish a panic attack from a heart attack or other serious condition, so please continue with this meditation only if you are completely sure what you are experiencing is strictly anxiety driven.

contents.name: Dealing with Pressure
contents.title: Dealing with Pressure
contents.description: Pressure to perform can be very stressful. When we are stressed, we are not working at our best, and may not achieve the results we desire. This guided meditation will give you techniques to help calm and relax both your body and your mind, enabling you to feel confident, capable and ready to tackle life’s challenges.

contents.name: Dealing with Guilt
contents.title: Dealing with Guilt
contents.description: Feelings of guilt come from a sense of responsibility for having done, or not done, something that’s created some negative emotions. Feelings of guilt can come from actual circumstances, but they can also be based on perceptions that have no basis in reality, just as children may feel a misguided sense of guilt about their parents divorce. This guided visualization will help you to bring awareness to the sources of feelings of guilt so you can let them go thru clarity, acceptance and forgiveness.

contents.name: Dealing with Menopause
contents.title: Dealing with Menopause
contents.description: Although many women resist this period of change in their lives, I like to think of menopause as a process of giving birth to yourself. As women, a good part of our lives has been devoted to caring for others. This period can symbolize the beginning of a time just for you, to nurture and care for yourself. And though the symptoms of menopause can be difficult, if you can view this as a metamorphosis into a new beautiful stage in your life, you may even be able to find a sense of new-found liberation, just like the butterfly.

contents.name: Pregnancy
contents.title: Pregnancy
contents.description: Your baby is capable of feeling your energy and the vibration of your positive thoughts. This visualization will help you connect with your baby in a calm and relaxed state, and to send thoughts of love to him or her.

contents.name: Managing PMS
contents.title: Managing PMS
contents.description: This guided visualization will help you cope with any physical discomfort or overwhelming emotions you may be dealing with during your cycle.

contents.name: Nurturing Creativity
contents.title: Nurturing Creativity
contents.description: We are all born with the ability to tap into a great well-spring of creativity. And though we never really lose that ability, we can sometimes forget how to access it, as our mental noise gets louder. This guided visualization will help you open the connection to the source of the pure creativity that resides within you.

contents.name: Developing Intuition
contents.title: Developing Intuition
contents.description: We are all born with the ability to be intuitive, and we never really lose that ability. It’s voice just seems to dim as our minds get noisier. This guided visualization will help you regain your connection with the intuition voice that resides within you.

contents.name: Trust
contents.title: Trust
contents.description: Practicing the affirmations in this meditation is like planting seeds deep in your subconsciousness. Each time you recall and repeat them to yourself, you are watering and nurturing them, and encouraging them to grow to fruition.

contents.name: Becoming More Accepting
contents.title: Becoming More Accepting
contents.description: Acceptance is really just allowing whatever is… to just be. This guided visualization will explore the feelings that prevent you from going with the flow.

contents.name: Feeling Compassion
contents.title: Feeling Compassion
contents.description: As humans, we are naturally hardwired to feel compassion. If we see someone stub their toe, we feel their pain. If a baby in a nursery starts to cry, other babies start to cry in sympathy. This is the natural compassion we all have within us. But sometimes, we get so self-absorbed in our own busy lives, that the natural compassion within us gets buried. This guided visualization will help bring to light that sense of compassion within you.

contents.name: Finding Forgiveness
contents.title: Finding Forgiveness
contents.description: There’s a wise expression that says holding anger toward someone is like drinking poison and expecting the other person to die. We often feel that the act of forgiveness is a gift to the other person, when in fact forgiveness, is really a gift to ourselves. Forgiveness is not about releasing the other person of responsibility for their actions. It’s about releasing the anger that can be so harmful to our well-being. This meditation will help you open your heart to the peace and love that lies within, allowing the spark of forgiveness to grow within you.

contents.name: Weight Loss
contents.title: Weight Loss
contents.description: Achieving the healthy body that you deserve requires positivity and determination, as well as a healthy lifestyle change. Use this meditation to help support you in this, as you progress on your path towards achieving your weight loss goals.

contents.name: Divorce
contents.title: Divorce
contents.description: Divorce can be a very painful process. Though it can initially be seen as a loss, it can also be seen as a transformation of a relationship. Just as the caterpillar doesn’t know the beauty it will eventually become, you too will eventually find a new beautiful form. This guided visualization will help you deal with the difficult emotions in this transitional period of your life.

contents.name: Dealing with a Break-Up
contents.title: Dealing with a Break-Up
contents.description: Break-ups can be very difficult and stressful. This meditation will help release negative emotions, and help you heal.

contents.name: Finding the Ideal Job
contents.title: Finding the Ideal Job
contents.description: We have the power to create our lives as we want them to be. But we must be very clear about what we want. And the more vividly we can visualize what we want, the stronger the force to create that vision becomes. Finding that perfect job is no different. This guided visualization will help you form a clear vision of the ideal job and set the intention to bring it into your life.

contents.name: Dealing with Rejection
contents.title: Dealing with Rejection
contents.description: We all experience feelings of rejection from time to time. Sometimes from actual circumstances, and sometimes from our own mind-made stories. But, in either case, we always have a choice about how to deal with it. If we take it personally, it can be very painful. But we always have the power to deal with these feelings in a non-personal way, and by doing so, we can make our lives a lot easier.

contents.name: My Boss Is a Jerk
contents.title: My Boss Is a Jerk
contents.description: Whether it’s someone in the workplace, at school or even in your family, we all have challenging people to deal with. Learning how to manage relationships with difficult people is something we can all use some help with. But it’s not so much that we need to learn how to deal with difficult people themselves, it’s more that we need to learn how to manage our own reactions without getting drawn into these conflicts. This guided visualization will give you some techniques to deal with challenging people in your life.

contents.name: Remembering a Loved One
contents.title: Remembering a Loved One
contents.description: Losing a loved one can be very painful, and if the loss was recent, our own feelings of sadness and grief can overshadow the feelings of love we feel for them.  But even if they aren’t with us physically anymore, they are always spiritually and emotionally present.  Connecting with our awareness of our emotions helps us to recognize that our feelings of sadness and grief come and go, but the love we shared lives on forever within us.

contents.name: Fight with Your Partner
contents.title: Fight with Your Partner
contents.description: Fighting with someone you love can be very painful. Living in close quarters and sharing so much history and time with someone can create pressure. When that pressure gets added to the pressures of daily life, it sometimes gets released in an explosive way. This visualization will help you connect to your feelings and your partner, and get back to that place of calm before the storm.

contents.name: My Busy Mind
contents.title: My Busy Mind
contents.description: This short guided meditation for young children introduces the idea that everybody has lots of thoughts, and it's OK to get distracted, and to just come back to the breath.

contents.name: Feeling My Body
contents.title: Feeling My Body
contents.description: This meditation is designed to help children become more in tune with their own bodies and to how they are feeling.

contents.name: Sounds All Around Us
contents.title: Sounds All Around Us
contents.description: This mediation is a useful tool to help your child become more in tune and aware of their environment by focusing their awareness on their sense of hearing.

contents.name: I Am a Mountain
contents.title: I Am a Mountain
contents.description: This descriptive visualization meditation will stimulate your child’s imagination, and affirm a sense of stability and self-empowerment.

contents.name: Body Scan
contents.title: Body Scan
contents.description: We have many feelings that can be felt in different parts of our body. Paying attention to our bodies can help us get to know how we're feeling. It also helps to release tension and quiet our minds.

contents.name: Being Myself
contents.title: Being Myself
contents.description: We all feel pressure from all around us to think and act in certain ways, it can sometimes be challenging to be able to maintain our individuality. This visualization will help empower you to be comfortable and confident being yourself.

contents.name: Feeling the Breath
contents.title: Feeling the Breath
contents.description: This simple breath meditation uses breath awareness to bring your mind and body together. Focusing on the breath helps relax your body and calm your mind.

contents.name: Better Focus for Tests
contents.title: Better Focus for Tests
contents.description: Preparing for, and taking tests and exams, can be very stressful. And often, the stress can get in the way of achieving results, even when you understand the stuff you’re studying. This guided visualization will help set the intention and the path to keeping calm, maintaining confidence, and creating a mindset of success.

contents.name: Floating on a Cloud
contents.title: Floating on a Cloud

contents.title: Peaceful Meadow
contents.description: Let this relaxing visualization ease away all the tension from your body and mind. You'll be left feeling completely relaxed, as you take an imaginary journey through a beautiful and peaceful meadow.

contents.name: Fear of Commitment
contents.title: Fear of Commitment
contents.description: Whether in terms of relationships, career or other major life events, making decisions with long-term implications can be difficult. There are many reasons that people often feel a sense of fear when faced with such decisions: Trust in themselves, fear of change, of being hurt, or being trapped, or sometimes it’s just procrastination. This guided visualization will help you overcome the fear of commitment and open the door to a feeling of courage and trust in yourself as you embark on this new adventure in your life’s journey…

contents.name: Learn the One Minute Meditation
contents.title: Learn the One Minute Meditation
contents.description: Do this meditation anywhere you like, and as often as you like during the day, to bring you back to the present moment. It only takes one minute and you can do it with your eyes open.

contents.name: Blanket of Love
contents.title: Blanket of Love
contents.description: Increase your compassion and feelings of love for yourself and the world around you with this meditation. It will leave you feeling relaxed and positive in just a few minutes.

contents.name: Loving Kindness
contents.title: Loving Kindness
contents.description: The Loving Kindness meditation has been shown to increase positive emotional responses like love, joy, hope, contentment and awe. It also reduces pain, and increases the grey matter of your brain.

contents.name: Relief from Chemotherapy
contents.title: Relief from Chemotherapy
contents.description: This guided visualization is to be used in conjunction with chemotherapy treatment. Using guided imagery of healing white light filling your body, let this meditation help to relax you and create a sense of positivity before, during or after treatment.

contents.name: Meditation Is Fun
contents.title: Meditation Is Fun
contents.description: Introduce your child to "becoming still" with this short guided meditation focused on the feeling of breathing in the body.

contents.name: Watching Your Breath
contents.title: Watching Your Breath
contents.description: Continuing to focus on the breath, this guided meditation will help your child become more comfortable sitting still.

contents.name: Can't Stop Thinking!
contents.title: Can't Stop Thinking!
contents.description: This meditation continues to teach young children the skill of paying attention to the breath as a way to calm their busy minds.

contents.name: Brain Break
contents.title: Brain Break
contents.description: Make meditation fun by calling it a "Brain Break". Just like we need to sleep at night to keep our bodies healthy, our brains also need a break to keep them healthy.

contents.name: Learn to Meditate
contents.title: Learn to Meditate
contents.description: Enjoy this introductory guided meditation for young teenagers.

contents.name: Me and My Breath
contents.title: Me and My Breath
contents.description: This meditation continues to introduce the young teenager to the basic skills of meditation, and meditation as a "Happy Place".

contents.name: Nothing to Do
contents.title: Nothing to Do
contents.description: Focusing on the idea of the "Brain Break", this meditation is a great way to teach young teenagers that meditation is a time for doing nothing at all.

contents.name: Calming Down
contents.title: Calming Down
contents.description: Continuing to explore the basic skills of meditation, this guided meditation helps young teenagers deal with restlessness, and teaches them that it's a perfectly normal feeling.

contents.name: Be Here Now
contents.title: Be Here Now
contents.description: An introductory meditation that helps youngsters appreciate the "Here & Now", and meditation as a way to take a "Brain Break" and to become fully present.

contents.name: Mindful Moment - Music
contents.title: Mindful Moment - Music
contents.description: Practice one minute of mindfulness anywhere you are, and as often as you like during the day, to bring you back to the present moment. It only takes one minute and you can do it with your eyes open.

contents.name: 1 Minute Meditation - Music
contents.title: 1 Minute Meditation - Music
contents.description: Do this meditation anywhere you like, and as often as you like during the day, to bring you back to the present moment. It only takes one minute and you can do it with your eyes open.

contents.name: 2 Minute Reliever - Music
contents.title: 2 Minute Reliever - Music
contents.description: Feeling anxious but only have two minutes? Use this short meditation to take the opportunity to de-stress and relax.  Your body and mind will thank you.

contents.name: 5 Minute Meditation - Music
contents.title: 5 Minute Meditation - Music
contents.description: Use this short meditation to give you that break you need in your busy day. You’ll be amazed at how refreshed you will feel after just 5 minutes.

contents.name: Family Blanket of Love
contents.title: Family Blanket of Love
contents.description: Do this meditation with the whole family. It's a great way to wind down together at the end of the day and connect with each other.

contents.name: Meditation for Couples
contents.title: Meditation for Couples
contents.description: This meditation is best done as a couple. Use this guided visualization to help you relax and connect with your inner self and to open up a channel of love and energy with your partner.

contents.name: Forgive Your Parents
contents.title: Forgive Your Parents
contents.description: Holding on to feelings of anger and resentment can put a huge strain on our health, wellbeing and our relationships, even if these emotions and feeling are justified. Use this meditation to help ‘let go’ of these feelings and clear the path for new understanding and connection.

contents.name: Embracing Change
contents.title: Embracing Change
contents.description: Change is something that happens continuously in life, yet some changes can be a bit more difficult to accept than others. Use this guided visualization to help ease the resistance to change within you, and to open the door to new perspectives that can help you flow with the changes in your life.

contents.name: Inner Courage
contents.title: Inner Courage
contents.description: Courage is the strength that drives us to try new things and push ourselves beyond our comfort zone into a world of new possibilities. Use this guided visualization to help connect with your inner fire, and tap into the sense of adventure and power that burns within you.

contents.name: Keeping Balance
contents.title: Keeping Balance
contents.description: There are so many different things pulling on us at all times. Career, family, personal responsibility…  it can be challenging to maintain a sense of balance and moderation as we struggle to meet the needs of those around us, as well as our own. Use this guided meditation to help find a deeper sense of balance within yourself, and to promote well-being and harmony in your life.

contents.name: My Family Drives Me Nuts
contents.title: My Family Drives Me Nuts
contents.description: We’ve all been there. We have the best of intentions. We love our families but somehow being around them for extended periods – like the holidays – has us regressing to old patterns and childhood behaviors that we wish to forget. This meditation will focus on how we can bring some awareness to our challenging family relationships, and approach them from a new positive perspective.

contents.name: Dealing with Holiday Stress
contents.title: Dealing with Holiday Stress
contents.description: The holidays are meant to be a time for celebration, however, the pressure of creating a relaxing and enjoyable holiday environment, and coming together with people who we love but who push our buttons, can sometimes be stressful. This guided visualization will help bring awareness to the obstacles that can prevent us from being able to relax and fully enjoy our holiday experience.

contents.name: Inside Beautiful, Outside Beautiful
contents.title: Inside Beautiful, Outside Beautiful
contents.description: We spend so much time trying to live up to others’ expectations of us and seeing ourselves through other people's eyes. As we give our outer appearance more and more of our attention, we can begin to lose touch with our own inner-beauty. This meditation will help you peel away the protective masks we wear for others, and allow you to re-connect with the source of love deep within you.

contents.name: Balance Breath
contents.title: Balance Breath
contents.description: Learn this simple breathing technique that you can use whenever you're feeling a bit out of balance and need to come back to center.

contents.name: Focus Breath
contents.title: Focus Breath
contents.description: This breathing technique can be done in just a few minutes whenever you need a bit more mental clarity. It's easy to learn and you can do it on your own anytime.

contents.name: Calming Breath
contents.title: Calming Breath
contents.description: Try this short breathing technique whenever you feel stressed or anxious. Easy to learn and keep in your toolbox!

contents.name: Energy Breath
contents.title: Energy Breath
contents.description: Give yourself a shot of energy and personal power with this rhythmic breathing technique known as the 'Breath of Fire'.

contents.name: Gratitude Breath
contents.title: Gratitude Breath
contents.description: This short meditation will help you stay positive by focusing on the things in your life that you love. Use this one daily, or whenever you find yourself focusing on what's missing instead of what's going right.

contents.name: Complete Breath
contents.title: Complete Breath
contents.description: When you're feeling overwhelmed or just need to feel a bit more refreshed, this is a great breathing technique to use. It creates a full circulation of new oxygen in your lungs and throughout your body.

contents.name: Emergency Breath
contents.title: Emergency Breath
contents.description: For those moments when you feel yourself becoming overwhelmed with strong feelings, this is a great breathing technique to learn and use in the moment.

contents.name: Ocean Breath
contents.title: Ocean Breath
contents.description: This is a great breathing technique to use when you're feeling nervous or anxious. It's really easy to learn and you can do it anytime and anywhere.

contents.name: Time Out
contents.title: Time Out
contents.description: This is a great one to use when you're feeling reactive and short on patience. It's also a great one to teach young kids to help them calm themselves when they get angry

contents.name: 5 Minute Body Scan
contents.title: 5 Minute Body Scan
contents.description: Try this short body scan meditation anytime you feel the need to clear your mind and relax your body.

contents.name: Time Out
contents.title: Time Out
contents.description: This is a great one to use when you’re feeling reactive and short on patience. It’s also a great one to teach young kids to help them calm themselves when they get angry.

contents.name: 5 Minute Abundance
contents.title: 5 Minute Abundance
contents.description: Enjoy this short meditation anytime you feel that sense of lack kicking in. You can find abundance everywhere if you start by finding it in your mind.

contents.name: 5 Minute Anxiety
contents.title: 5 Minute Anxiety
contents.description: If you're feeling anxious and only have a few minutes to spare, this meditation is just what you need. See how your breath can take you out of your worries, and into the present moment.

contents.name: 5 Minute Focus
contents.title: 5 Minute Focus
contents.description: Use this 5 minute meditation anytime you need an extra dose of clarity and focus.

contents.name: 5 Minute Intention
contents.title: 5 Minute Intention
contents.description: Keep your life on track with the power of intention. The short meditation will help you keep your intentions at the forefront of your mind.

contents.name: 5 Minute Gratitude
contents.title: 5 Minute Gratitude
contents.description: Give yourself a 5 minute shot of calm, with a side order of appreciation. You may start seeing your life from a fresh new perspective.

contents.name: 5 Minute Kindness
contents.title: 5 Minute Kindness
contents.description: When you're looking to bring a bit more kindness in, and you only have a few minutes to spare, this meditation is just the thing.

contents.name: 5 Minute Balance
contents.title: 5 Minute Balance
contents.description: In our busy, multi-tasking world, staying in balance has become more challenging. This 5 minute meditation will help you find a bit more equilibrium in your life.

contents.name: 5 Minute Creativity
contents.title: 5 Minute Creativity
contents.description: Enjoy this short meditation anytime you need to get those creative juices flowing. Your creative wellspring is always accessible, just behind your thoughts.

contents.name: 5 Minute - Crazy World
contents.title: 5 Minute - Crazy World
contents.description: Let this guided visualization help you find peace and acceptance when the world seems like an overwhelming and crazy place to live.

contents.name: Loving Yourself
contents.title: Loving Yourself
contents.description: To be open to give and receive love, we first have to love ourselves. This visualization will help you create a comfortable and loving space for self-acceptance and compassion.

contents.name: Discover Your Life Purpose
contents.title: Discover Your Life Purpose
contents.description: Have you ever felt there is something you are meant to be doing but you haven’t figured it out yet? This visualization will help you calm your active mind so you can better hear the soft voice of your intuition and get in touch with your life purpose.

contents.name: Chakra Meditation
contents.title: Chakra Meditation
contents.description: This meditation is designed to bring balance to the energy centers, or chakras, that dwell within you. When your life force is balanced, your health and vitality can thrive.

contents.name: Animal Farm
contents.title: Animal Farm
contents.description:
Listen carefully and see how many different farm sounds you can hear. This will help you practice paying attention and becoming more aware of the sounds around you in your daily life.

There are 18 sounds to find: farm ambience, barn sounds, feeding chickens, pigs, goat, tractor, cows, horse, human whistle, horse galloping, horse eating, footsteps, sheep, ducks, wooden gate opening, wooden door closing, dog barking and a rooster.

contents.name: Beach Walk
contents.title: Beach Walk
contents.description:
Use this track to fine-tune your mindful listening skills. See how many different beach sounds you can hear.   

There are 18 sounds to find: distant ocean ambience, seagulls, footsteps in the sand, bird, airplane passing by, waves, footsteps in water, sea lion, splash, wings, albatross, footsteps in deep water, underwater ambience, whale, boat horn, dolphin, wind, footsteps on sand and wood.

contents.name: Forest Life
contents.title: Forest Life
contents.description:
Fine-tune your mindful listening skills and see how many different forest sounds you can hear. This will help you practice paying attention to the sounds that are continually around you in your daily life.  

There are 18 sounds to find: forest ambience, woodpecker, footsteps in the grass, owl, bird, goose, wind in the trees, footsteps in the grass and on a bridge, small river and frogs, rock splash in the water, crickets ambience, coyote howl, airplane passing by in the distance, a calm bird, loon, distant thunder and rain.

contents.name: Jungle Cruise
contents.title: Jungle Cruise
contents.description:
Listen carefully and see how many different jungle sounds you can hear. This will help you practice mindful listening.

There are 16 sounds to find: jungle ambience, monkey call, bird 1, bird 2, lion in the distance, rain, footsteps, frogs, sound of trees moving, waterfall, boat passing, calm waves, canoe rowing, canoe moving, footsteps in the water and footsteps in the grass.

contents.name: Rapunzel
contents.title: Rapunzel
contents.description: Let this classic tale of the hero archetype be a soothing transition between the busy day you’ve left behind, and the restful night ahead. Get yourself comfortable and enjoy the story as you allow yourself to drift off to sleep.

contents.name: The Golden Goose
contents.title: The Golden Goose
contents.description: "The Golden Goose" is a story that illustrates the power of kindness and the Karmic circle it creates. Find a restful position, press play, and let a peaceful sleep come take you away.

contents.name: The Fisherman and His Wife
contents.title: The Fisherman and His Wife
contents.description: Say farewell to the day behind you and fall asleep to this classic tale on the themes of abundance and gratitude. Let your body relax as the fisherman and his wife illustrate how the practice of appreciation can help us to get off the treadmill of always searching for bigger, better and more.

contents.name: Coping with Grief
contents.title: Coping with Grief
contents.description: The tendency to want to push away feelings like grief and pain is a perfectly normal response. In this meditation you'll learn to allow grief in so it will have less of a stranglehold on you.

contents.name: Simply Allowing
contents.title: Simply Allowing
contents.description: Allowing life to unfold and trusting in the process can be difficult for many of us in a society that values hard work and achievement. This meditation is designed to help you find that balance.

contents.name: Finding Serenity
contents.title: Finding Serenity
contents.description: In this meditation you'll learn to stay calm and serene, even when life throws a challenge at you. And it will.

contents.name: Connecting with Stillness
contents.title: Connecting with Stillness
contents.description: Use this meditation to find some peace and stillness whenever you need that break from the hustle and bustle of life.

contents.name: De-stress at Your Desk
contents.title: De-stress at Your Desk
contents.description: For those moments at work when you are feeling the stress accumulate. Learn to de-stress, right there at your desk.

contents.name: Relaxing into Life
contents.title: Relaxing into Life
contents.description: Much of the pain and suffering in our life comes from holding onto things too long. In this meditation, you'll develop the skill of letting go and relaxing into the flow of life.

contents.name: Staying Sharp
contents.title: Staying Sharp
contents.description: Keeping your mind sharp is obviously important when it comes to navigating your way through life. So use this meditation to decrease stress and help stimulate your focus.

contents.name: Liberation from Addiction
contents.title: Liberation from Addiction
contents.description: If you're struggling with addiction in your life, use this meditation to help support you as you make the changes you need to release yourself and build a new future.

contents.name: Re-boot your Focus
contents.title: Re-boot your Focus
contents.description: As you are guided through this meditation, you will learn to perform a complete body scan. This will help you improve your ability to concentrate and direct your focus.

contents.name: Energize your Mind
contents.title: Energize your Mind
contents.description: This meditation is perfect for those moments when you're just not feeling mentally sharp and you could use some refreshing. It's an easy one to master and you can use it anytime, anywhere.

contents.name: Master your Memory
contents.title: Master your Memory
contents.description: If you're looking to sharpen your mental focus and improve your memory, then this is the meditation for you. It's a simple technique that has a great effect.

contents.name: A Man's Purpose
contents.title: A Man's Purpose
contents.description: Relax and drift off to sleep as you enjoy this age old story about finding purpose and creating a life of happiness and joy.

contents.name: Soul Sweeper
contents.title: Soul Sweeper
contents.description: "Soul Sweeper" is a story that shows us that peace and happiness are often closer than you think. Find a comfortable position and let this old tale take you into a deep and restful sleep.

contents.name: De-stress at Your Desk
contents.title: De-stress at Your Desk
contents.description: For those moments at work when you are feeling the stress accumulate.  Learn to de-stress, right there at your desk.

contents.name: Be More Loving
contents.title: Be More Loving
contents.description: Let yourself be guided in an awakening of positive, loving emotion. This meditation will encourage and foster a caring and loving energy for all the people in your life, including yourself.

contents.name: Turning Around Negative Reactions
contents.title: Turning Around Negative Reactions
contents.description: Clear your mind and heart of any negative thoughts and feelings and learn to just let them float away.

contents.name: Simplifying Life
contents.title: Simplifying Life
contents.description: Is life feeling too busy? Too complicated and demanding? The best way to simplify your life is to start with your mindset. This meditation will encourage you to live in the moment and not be so overwhelmed by things that have not yet come to pass.

contents.name: Meditation For The Environment
contents.title: Meditation For The Environment
contents.description: This meditation is designed to help you tap into the wonderful and amazing interconnectedness of all life on our beautiful Earth. From the oceans to the trees, we are all working together, supporting each other... come feel that connection.

contents.name: Surrendering
contents.title: Surrendering
contents.description: Come let go of everything holding you back from relaxing on the deepest level, so you can be light and at ease.

contents.name: Chronic pain
contents.title: Chronic pain
contents.description: If you suffer from chronic pain, use this meditation to find comfort and relief, and learn how to manage your pain in a new way.

contents.name: Relief from Migraines
contents.title: Relief from Migraines
contents.description: This meditation is especially made to help you find relief from the pain and discomfort of migraines.

contents.name: Middle Of The Night Worries
contents.title: Middle Of The Night Worries
contents.description: Use this meditation if you find yourself awake with worry in the middle of the night and are having trouble sleeping. Relax and drift off to a deep and peaceful slumber.

contents.name: Pride and Prejudice
contents.title: Pride and Prejudice
contents.description: Come fall asleep to Jane Austen's classic tale, which touches on the themes of judgment, acceptance and perspective. Get yourself comfortable and prepare to drift off to a deep and peaceful sleep.

contents.name: Calm Your Worrisome Thoughts
contents.title: Calm Your Worrisome Thoughts
contents.description: It's normal to think deeply about things, but sometimes out thoughts won't let us rest. This meditation is for those times when you need to relax your mind and calm your worries.

contents.name: Resolving Internal Conflict
contents.title: Resolving Internal Conflict
contents.description: We often find ourselves at a crossroads in our journey through this life. It's not always easy to make a choice, and this can cause internal conflict and worry. If you find yourself in a similar place, use this meditation to lose your fear and uncertainty and resolve this conflict so you can move forward.

contents.name: Effective Communication
contents.title: Effective Communication
contents.description: Effective communication is the glue that keeps our relationships in harmony. And one of the most significant ways you can enhance your communication is to become an amazing listener. Use this visualization to improve how you express yourself and to open yourself up to truly listen to the needs of others.

contents.name: Dealing With Fear Of Missing Out
contents.title: Dealing With Fear Of Missing Out
contents.description: The fear of missing out is a type of anxiety that causes stress and mental discomfort. It also prevents you from experiencing and enjoying what is happening around you in the present moment. In this meditation, we focus on calming this state of anxiety as well as cultivating mindfulness to help overcome this fear.
contents.short_title: Dealing With Fear Of Missing Out

contents.name: Slowing Down
contents.title: Slowing Down
contents.description: This is a visualization for you to use when you want to slow down and relax from your worries and responsibilities. Come release any tension and find some peace and tranquility.

contents.name: Finding Self-Discipline
contents.title: Finding Self-Discipline
contents.description: Making changes in our lives is not always the easiest thing. Even when the changes will improve your life. This meditation is meant to help you strengthen and develop your self-discipline so you can achieve your goals and let go of old patterns of behavior that don't serve you.

contents.name: Coping with Illness
contents.title: Coping with Illness
contents.description: This meditation will help you connect with and invite a healing and purifying energy into your body. You'll learn to use the power of visualization to soothe and cleanse, and help dissolve any tension or discomfort you may be experiencing.

contents.name: Dealing with Frustration
contents.title: Dealing with Frustration
contents.description: Anger and frustration are normal emotions, and managing these feelings doesn't mean hiding them away or pretending they don't exist. It's about acknowledging and accepting them when they arise, yet choosing to not be overwhelmed or controlled by them. This meditation is designed to help you do just that.

contents.name: Connecting to Purpose
contents.title: Connecting to Purpose
contents.description: Every experience you have had in your unique journey here on Earth has helped to shape who you are.  And so this meditation is designed to help you connect to the purpose and meaning of your life as you move along your path.

contents.name: Moby Dick
contents.title: Moby Dick

contents.name: The Art of Bread-Making

contents.name: Being Treated Unfairly
contents.title: Being Treated Unfairly

contents.name: Social Anxiety
contents.title: Social Anxiety

contents.name: Death of a Parent
contents.title: Death of a Parent

contents.name: Dealing with Chronic Illness
contents.title: Dealing with Chronic Illness

contents.name: Health Anxiety

contents.name: PMS Anxiety

contents.name: Self-destructive Behavior

contents.name: Dealing with Impatience

contents.title: Accepting your Busy Mind

contents.name: Day 1 - Give Sleep a Chance
contents.title: Day 1 - Give Sleep a Chance
contents.description:
Better Sleep Series - Take Your Meditation to Bed

In this 7 day series, we explore how your meditation practice can help you enjoy better nights' sleep. Using the same techniques from your meditation practice, you'll learn how to develop better 'sleep hygiene', and to counteract the anxious thinking that keeps many of us up at night.

Day 1 - The funny thing about sleep is, the harder you try the more elusive it becomes. This meditation will help you if your busy mind just isn't cooperating with your desire to fall asleep.

contents.name: Day 2 - Put Your Expectations to Bed
contents.title: Day 2 - Put Your Expectations to Bed
contents.description: Do you sometimes stress about not getting enough sleep? This anxiety actually works to keep you awake. This meditation will help you let go of your expectations regarding sleep so you can let go of any stress and anxiety and let sleep come to you.
contents.short_title: Day 2 - Put Your Expectations to Bed

contents.name: Day 3 - You Are Not Your Thoughts
contents.title: Day 3 - You Are Not Your Thoughts
contents.description: Our thoughts are so powerful that they can prevent us from finding the restful sleep we need. This meditation invites you to try stepping back from your thoughts to view them with a bit of detachment. This practice will help you find the calm you need to drift off into sleep each night.
contents.short_title: Day 3 - You Are Not Your Thoughts

contents.name: Day 4 - One Night at a Time
contents.title: Day 4 - One Night at a Time
contents.description: Having trouble finding the off button at night? It's often because our minds are busy obsessing over future or past events. This meditation will help you learn to take control of your mind and bring it back to the present moment. This makes the transition into a peaceful sleep much, much easier.
contents.short_title: Day 4 - One Night at a Time

contents.name: Day 5 - Surrender to Sleep
contents.title: Day 5 - Surrender to Sleep
contents.description: To break the cycle of sleeplessness, you first have to accept it without worrying whether it is 'good' or 'bad'. This will help keep you from resisting your sleeplessness, which only makes it worse. Join me in this meditation to learn to accept 'what is' and find rest through surrender.

contents.name: Day 6 - Gratitude Strikes Again
contents.title: Day 6 - Gratitude Strikes Again
contents.description: Do you expect to fall asleep right away each night? Expectations like this can cause frustration if they don't go as planned. This meditation will guide you to replace your expectations with expressions of gratitude instead. This can liberate you from frustrations and leave you with a sense of contentment.

contents.name: Day 7 -  What’s Keeping You up at Night
contents.title: Day 7 -  What’s Keeping You up at Night
contents.description: As you bring more awareness to how your daily life affects your sleep, you become more in sync with what your mind and body needs to really let go. As you pay attention to this, you'll notice which patterns no longer serve you. Remember, changing your habits can take time, so be patient with yourself.
contents.short_title: Day 7 -  What’s Keeping You up at Night

contents.name: Day 1 - Where Does Stress Come From?
contents.title: Day 1 - Where Does Stress Come From?
contents.description:
Stress Less! Series - Don't Stress About It

This week, we put stress under the microscope. We'll explore the nature and sources of much of our stress, and you'll see how much of it you actually have some control over. We'll explore how you can lessen your stress thru simple meditation techniques. 

Day 1 - The first step in releasing your stress is understanding where it comes from. If you pay attention to how your mind works, you'll see your stress probably comes from fears of the future. This meditation will help you bring awareness to this and back to the present moment where there is no stress or fear.
contents.short_title: Day 1 - Where Does Stress Come From?

contents.name: Day 2 - Inner Turmoil/Outer Turmoil
contents.title: Day 2 - Inner Turmoil/Outer Turmoil
contents.description: Your mind and body are intimately connected. So when you are mentally stressed, your body is likely to be tense as well. This meditation will help you develop control over how you deal with your stress and find balance no matter what life throws at you.

contents.name: Day 3 - You Have It in You
contents.title: Day 3 - You Have It in You
contents.description: It can be easy to think you need to look outside of yourself for a solution to your stress. The truth is, you always have all that you need. Stress and anxiety require our minds to be in the future, and they disappear when we connect to the present moment. This meditation will help you do just that.
contents.short_title: Day 3 - You Have It in You

contents.name: Day 4 - Letting Go of the Reins
contents.title: Day 4 - Letting Go of the Reins
contents.description: Our expectations in life are a very common source of stress. They imply a sense of being owed something, which can leave you feeling a bit 'ripped off' when they're not met. A less stressful way to live is to focus on goals, which give you direction in life instead. This meditation explores this subtle but important distinction.
contents.short_title: Day 4 - Letting Go of the Reins

contents.name: Day 5 - What We Resist Persists
contents.title: Day 5 - What We Resist Persists
contents.description: You might be amazed how much your stress disappears when you bring a sense of acceptance of 'what is' into your life. Rather than resist and hold onto expectations, we learn to let go and go with the flow in this important meditation.

contents.name: Day 6 - Cut Yourself Some Slack
contents.title: Day 6 - Cut Yourself Some Slack
contents.description: One of the dangers of stress is it can cause us to do the very things that make it worse. This meditation will help you notice your triggers and patterns so you can catch them before they escalate and give yourself some TLC instead.

contents.name: Day 7 -  Perspectives
contents.title: Day 7 -  Perspectives
contents.description: Did you know the Chinese language uses the same character for both 'crisis' and 'opportunity'? That's because it is a matter of perspective and how you decide to respond to a life event. This meditation will help you take a step back from your own personal story so you can see other perspectives and better manage stressful situations.

contents.name: Day 1 - Stepping Back
contents.title: Day 1 - Stepping Back
contents.description:
Feeling Happier Series - Melt Away Those Blues

Enjoy these 7 daily, guided meditations focused on getting in touch with what truly makes you happy. Learn how the practice of presence - both in meditation and in daily life - can be the doorway to new-found happiness.

Day 1 - Sometimes it can feel like our emotions take us on a roller-coaster ride and we just have to hang on. This meditation will help you learn to take a step back from your emotions so you won't be so at their mercy. The more you do this, the more you come to see that you are not your emotions and you can change your relationship to them.

contents.name: Day 2 - Happiness Is Present
contents.title: Day 2 - Happiness Is Present
contents.description: As you learn to create a distance between you and your emotions, you can better observe their nature. From this position, you can come to see how feelings of unhappiness are usually rooted in either the past or the future. This meditation will help you be more present in the moment by bringing your mind and body together.

contents.name: Day 3 - Weathering the Storm
contents.title: Day 3 - Weathering the Storm
contents.description: Emotions can be like the weather, and storm clouds come and go. This meditation will help you see that you are the sky, not the clouds. You are bigger than your emotions, and with practice you can maintain a peaceful stillness in your life.

contents.name: Day 4 - Staying With the Feelings
contents.title: Day 4 - Staying With the Feelings
contents.description: One of the benefits of meditation is that we become more in touch with our thoughts and feelings, and how we relate to them. We're not trying to make your feelings go away, we're trying to soften your relationship to them. This meditation will help you gain that distance between you and your feelings so you can take them less personally.

contents.name: Day 5 - Finding Light in the Darkness
contents.title: Day 5 - Finding Light in the Darkness
contents.description: It's a normal response to want to bury or suppress painful emotions. But this is not the way to long-lasting happiness. This meditation will help you find the courage to look at and accept your challenging emotions. After all, only the light of day can get rid of the darkness.
contents.short_title: Day 5 - Finding Light in the Darkness

contents.name: Day 6 - Kind Over Matter
contents.title: Day 6 - Kind Over Matter
contents.description: Kindness is contagious, and it's also an antidote to unhappiness. The tricky thing is... it doesn't come naturally to want to go out of our way for others, when we're in a bad place ourselves. This meditation will help you get in touch with your natural kindness so you can give yourself the gift of happiness as you spread it to those around you.

contents.name: Day 7 - The Big Picture
contents.title: Day 7 - The Big Picture
contents.description: Our happiness in life is very much a result of how connected we are to the people in our lives. It's also a result of expanding our sense of self beyond our simple thoughts and emotions. Today's meditation builds on these two themes of connection and expansion and how they affect our happiness.

contents.name: Day 1 - Staying in the Here and Now
