contents.title: Day 1 - Staying in the Here and Now
contents.description:
Relationship Harmony Series - Getting to the Root of Conflict

This week, we'll look at how the skills we learned in meditation can help you deal better with relationship conflict and bring more harmony into your life. Focusing on self-awareness, we'll look at how our automatic reactions can be replaced with calm conscious actions.

Day 1 - Relationships can be one of our greatest sources of joy, but they can also be the source of much of our pain and conflict. This can occur when we get caught up in the emotional turmoil of our past stories or our projections into the future. So one key to creating harmony with the loved ones in your life is to stay connected to what's happening in the present moment. This meditation is designed to help you do just that.
contents.short_title: Day 1 - Staying in the Here and Now

contents.name: Day 2 - Knowing Our Stories
contents.title: Day 2 - Knowing Our Stories
contents.description: We all carry stories with us. From previous relationships, from how we were raised, and from our life experiences. By understanding our own personal stories better, we come to learn how they affect our way of relating. This meditation will help you take a step back and observe your reactivity patterns with some objectivity. From this space, you can then make a conscious choice of how you want to act.

contents.name: Day 3 - Dropping Judgment
contents.title: Day 3 - Dropping Judgment
contents.description: The topic of this meditation is judgment. We all make judgments all day long, from the weather to the faces of the people we pass in the streets. It can be easy to take our judgments as truth, but it's really just another part of our story. By stepping back from judgment and simply noticing instead, you can invite more harmony into your relationships.

contents.name: Day 4 - Don't Take It Personally
contents.title: Day 4 - Don't Take It Personally
contents.description: Have you ever noticed how often conflict with others arises when we take things personally? When you do this, you might even feel under attack. This meditation will help you learn to let go and stop taking things so personally.

contents.name: Day 5 - Let It Go
contents.title: Day 5 - Let It Go
contents.description: One of the most important ways to increase harmony in any relationship is to truly listen to what the other person has to say. People can tell when you are giving them your full attention and this opens the door for real growth and understanding. This meditation works to help you build this wonderful relationship skill in your own life.

contents.name: Day 6 - Put It in Perspective
contents.title: Day 6 - Put It in Perspective
contents.description: It's so easy to get swept away by our own interpretation of events, that we don't process other points of view. The ability to see things from different perspectives is vital for maintaining and building harmony in your relationships. This meditation will help you learn to take the moments you need so you have the space to consider the way others are seeing things.

contents.name: Day 7 - Finding Compassion
contents.title: Day 7 - Finding Compassion
contents.description: Everyone has their own story which causes them to react the way they do. So when you take the time to notice your own inner stories, you create the opportunity to choose not to react in habitual ways. There's an old saying:  "Be kind. For everyone is fighting a battle you know nothing about". This meditation will help you develop compassion for those around you so you can then interact with more peaceful harmony.

contents.name: Day 1 - Stepping Back
contents.title: Day 1 - Stepping Back
contents.description:
Mindfulness & Social Media Series - Using Technology Mindfully

Technology and social media are here to stay, and are becoming an increasingly important part of our lives. This week, you'll enjoy relaxing guided meditations focused on using these tools in a balanced and mindful way.

Day 1 - It's easy to get lost in social media and today's amazing technology. Bringing a bit of awareness to how we use technology is the first step to taking back some of its power over us. This meditation will encourage you to take a step back and choose whether you want to respond to a notification or not.

contents.name: Day 2 - Finding Balance
contents.title: Day 2 - Finding Balance
contents.description: Bringing awareness to your interactions with technology can shed light on how your moods might be affected by it. And awareness is the first step in making changes and bringing more balance into your life. This meditation explores this topic so you don't become a "tool of your own tool".

contents.name: Day 3 - Noticing Judgment
contents.title: Day 3 - Noticing Judgment
contents.description: Have you ever found yourself comparing your life to that which you see in other people's social media feeds. Remember, those pictures are usually the carefully chosen highlights, and the comparison game will likely only lead to anxiety, stress and self-judgment. This meditation will help you bring a bit more awareness to the experience to allow you to notice how it's making you feel, so you can decide how often you want to engage.

contents.name: Day 4 - Using All Our Senses
contents.title: Day 4 - Using All Our Senses
contents.description: Are you really making a conscious choice to pick up your phone or check your Facebook or Instagram feeds? Or are you just habitually filling gaps of time to keep you from being bored. This meditation invites you to reconsider what you think of as boredom and instead see those moments as an opportunity to connect with yourself in a new way.

contents.name: Day 5 - It Starts With Intention
contents.title: Day 5 - It Starts With Intention
contents.description: If we're not careful, social media can consume a lot of our precious time or cause anxiety if we get caught up comparing our lives with others. The solution is to consciously set your intention before you do anything. This helps you to stay on track to where you really want to go. This meditation explores this topic further and helps you start a habit of setting intentions in your life.

contents.name: Day 6 - Not Always as It Seems
contents.title: Day 6 - Not Always as It Seems
contents.description: Believe it or not, social media can actually cause depression in some people. This has its roots in the need for external approval from others, or in feelings of inadequacy about our own lives. This meditation further explores how you can re-frame the way you value yourself and break the cycle of comparison.
contents.short_title: Day 6 - Not Always as It Seems

contents.name: Day 7 - Connections
contents.title: Day 7 - Connections
contents.description: Social media is a tool like any other tool. It's how we wield it that is important. Rather than use it mindlessly, this meditation will help you approach it with conscious intention and mindful awareness. That way you can find yourselves more in touch with your authentic self and more likely to use it in ways that serve you better.

contents.name: Day 1 - Habit or Hunger?
contents.title: Day 1 - Habit or Hunger?
contents.description:
Weight Loss Series - A New Approach to Losing Weight

This week, we'll explore how feelings and emotions lie at the root of our eating habits. These relaxing guided meditations will give you a new perspective about your motivations, as well as some great tips to bring mindfulness into your relationship with food.

Day 1 - One of the first steps in using meditation for weight loss is learning the difference between habit and real hunger. There are many factors that can cause you to overeat and this meditation will help bring awareness to your eating choices so you can make healthy decisions.

contents.name: Day 2 - What Do You Really Want?
contents.title: Day 2 - What Do You Really Want?
contents.description: Getting in touch with your intentions and your genuine motivation is the key to making successful changes in your life. This meditation will help you get in touch with your intentions and create an environment to best support your efforts to lose weight.
contents.short_title: Day 2 - What Do You Really Want?

contents.name: Day 3 - Judgment
contents.title: Day 3 - Judgment
contents.description: Studies have shown that there is a direct relationship between how we think about our bodies and our overall health. This meditation will help you connect with your physical body on a deeper level and become aware of the signals it is giving you.

contents.name: Day 4 - Thoughts
contents.title: Day 4 - Thoughts
contents.description: Have you ever taken notice of the inner dialogue that goes on in your mind? Especially those thoughts related to eating. This meditation will help you develop awareness of this internal chatter so you can become less reactive and more conscious with your decision making.

contents.name: Day 5 - Emotions
contents.title: Day 5 - Emotions
contents.description: The next step in your weight loss effort is to identify and understand the emotions you have attached to food. This meditation will help you develop awareness of these emotional triggers that could be causing you to overeat or make food choices that don't support your intentions.

contents.name: Day 6 - Perceptions
contents.title: Day 6 - Perceptions
contents.description: For many people, making changes in their diet can make them feel like they're lacking something. This often causes them to go back to their old ways. By practicing gratitude, you cultivate a perspective of abundance instead. This meditation will go into this important concept more deeply.

contents.name: Day 7 - Bringing It All Together
contents.title: Day 7 - Bringing It All Together
contents.description: Meditation can be a powerful tool to lose weight because it helps you become aware of the patterns that are preventing you from change. This meditation brings together all the concepts we have discussed in this series and will empower you to make healthy, conscious choices in your life.

contents.name: Day 1 - What Do You Want?
contents.title: Day 1 - What Do You Want?
contents.description:
Getting What You Want Series - Our Deepest Desires

Many people don't get what they want simply because they don't know what they're looking for. This week, you'll get in touch with what it is you desire at your deepest levels and find that it may be closer than you know.

Day 1 - Are you ready to get what you really want in life? It's easy to dream, but realizing those dreams is another thing altogether. This meditation will help you tune in to what truly makes you happy, and bring more awareness to beliefs that may be standing in your way.

contents.name: Day 2 - What's Your Intention?
contents.title: Day 2 - What's Your Intention?
contents.description: In this meditation, we'll go deeper into exploring your intentions and you'll ask yourself some important questions that will guide you in setting them. We'll explore how expectations can lead to disappointment and how to get out of this cycle by learning to let go.

contents.name: Day 3 - Trusting the Process
contents.title: Day 3 - Trusting the Process
contents.description: Your intentions for what you want in life are much like seeds that you plant in the soil. For these to become a flourishing garden, you need to give them the right conditions to grow. This meditation will help you stay connected to the intentions you set for yourself so that you stay on course throughout each day.

contents.name: Day 4 - Living Abundance
contents.title: Day 4 - Living Abundance
contents.description: Keeping your momentum going towards that which you want is easier when you stay connected with your intentions. So this meditation is designed to help you take note of the things in your life that support you and help you stay aligned with what makes you happy.

contents.name: Day 5 - Goals vs. Intentions
contents.title: Day 5 - Goals vs. Intentions
contents.description: This meditation explores the differences between goals and intentions and the different roles they each play in helping you get what you want in life. The distinction is important and will help guide you towards what you want in life.

contents.name: Day 6 - Authenticity
contents.title: Day 6 - Authenticity
contents.description: In this meditation, we continue our discussion and exploration of the power of intention. We look at how awareness of your intentions will help you choose how you want to respond to the events in your life rather than react unconsciously.

contents.name: Day 7 - An Inside Job
contents.title: Day 7 - An Inside Job
contents.description: This series, and getting what you want, is really about being happy. Genuine happiness. So in this meditation, we explore the idea that meaningful and lasting happiness can only be found within you.

contents.name: Day 1 - Yums and Tucks
contents.title: Day 1 - Yums and Tucks
contents.description:
It's interesting to see how the more we resist life events the more stress we actually feel. It appears counter-intuitive, but yet the only thing we can control in our lives are our own reactions. We often resist things that have already happened, or live in fear of what may happen. And that keeps us stuck holding on to what might have been or what we hope might be. This week we'll spend time recognizing 'what is' and we'll practice the art of letting go. The more we practice this, the more vibrant and alive we feel. So let's get started.

Day 1 - Our expectations are very often at the root of our suffering and our disappointments. In this meditation you'll practice being at peace with 'whatever is', rather than focusing on making judgements of 'good' or 'bad'.

contents.name: Day 2 - Stepping Back
contents.title: Day 2 - Stepping Back
contents.description: In this meditation, you'll continue to practice stepping back from the entanglement of your thoughts. This space gives you the opportunity to see what it is that you may be holding onto that just doesn't serve you anymore.

contents.name: Day 3 - Control
contents.title: Day 3 - Control
contents.description: It's natural to want to control everything in your life, but this is just not possible. Life is unpredictable and uncertain, and trying to control it will only lead to stress and anxiety. We pick where we left off last time with our practice of learning to accept life as it is.

contents.name: Day 4 - Fighting the Current
contents.title: Day 4 - Fighting the Current
contents.description: Most of us fight hard against the inevitable, and fight hard against change. But change is certain, and you'll find peace by accepting and embracing this fact. Let's explore this topic on a deeper level in this meditation and embrace life as it is.

contents.name: Day 5 - Obstacles
contents.title: Day 5 - Obstacles
contents.description: As we continue to explore our attachments in today's meditation, we'll look at three obstacles that stand in your way of being able to let things go.

contents.name: Day 6 - Surrender
contents.title: Day 6 - Surrender
contents.description: In today's meditation we'll explore the idea of surrender as part of the letting go process. Letting go of the struggle and allowing our hearts to open and soften.

contents.name: Day 7 - The Gift of Letting Go
contents.title: Day 7 - The Gift of Letting Go
contents.description: The beautiful thing about meditation is it allows you to develop the space to consciously choose how you want to react to the situations in your life. In the final meditation for this week, we'll explore the specific ways you can choose to react.
contents.short_title: Day 7 - The Gift of Letting Go

contents.name: Day 1 - Underlying Beliefs
contents.title: Day 1 - Underlying Beliefs
contents.description:
For most of us, quitting an addiction and changing our habits can be a huge challenge.  

This 7 day series is meant to support you by bringing awareness to your underlying beliefs so that you can then influence your unconscious mind and unleash yourself.

Day 1 – In today's meditation you will begin to become conscious of your decision making, so you can change your relationship to your particular addiction.

contents.name: Day 2 - Your Perspective
contents.title: Day 2 - Your Perspective
contents.description: The thing about experiences is that they are really neither 'good' or 'bad'. It's our own personal perspective that gives them a label.  We will explore this important concept in today's meditation.

contents.name: Day 3 - The Illusion of Control
contents.title: Day 3 - The Illusion of Control
contents.description: This meditation will encourage you to think about the illusion and control and the slippery slope that often follows a seemingly innocuous indulgence.

contents.name: Day 4 - Understanding Habits
contents.title: Day 4 - Understanding Habits
contents.description: In today's meditation we seek to bring more awareness to your habits and the underlying beliefs you may have about them. This allows you to examine them to see how they may be affecting your life.

contents.name: Day 5 - Light in the Darkness
contents.title: Day 5 - Light in the Darkness
contents.description: Some emotions we embrace and some we try to push away. This meditation will explore the potential ramifications of such actions and encourage you to learn to 'be' with all of your emotions.

contents.name: Day 6 - Being with Your Emotions
contents.title: Day 6 - Being with Your Emotions
contents.description: In today's meditation, we continue to explore your relationship to your emotions and you learn to get more in touch with them and how they may be affecting you.

contents.name: Day 7 - Urge Surfing
contents.title: Day 7 - Urge Surfing
contents.description: The final meditation in the series on addictions introduces the concept of 'urge surfing' and how this can give you tools to deal with any challenging cravings you may have.

contents.name: Day 1 - Setting your Intention
contents.title: Day 1 - Setting your Intention
contents.description:
Parenting is one of the greatest challenges we can undertake in this life. So this 7 day series is meant to support your growth as a parent to foster more mindfulness, understanding and compassion.

Day 1 – In today's meditation you will set your intentions for becoming a more mindful parent and consider the big picture for your family.

contents.name: Day 2 - Noticing your Internal States
contents.title: Day 2 - Noticing your Internal States
contents.description: Day Two is all about taking time to notice your internal states. This practice allows you to learn how to be less reactive and more considerate in your responses to family drama.

contents.name: Day 3 - Noticing the Pause
contents.title: Day 3 - Noticing the Pause
contents.description: In today's meditation we will be practicing the 'pause'. This moment, between stimulus and response, is your chance to choose your response. And in that response, lies your chance for growth.

contents.name: Day 4 - Your Habitual Patterns
contents.title: Day 4 - Your Habitual Patterns
contents.description: Bringing awareness to your habitual patterns is the theme for today's meditation. Doing so allows you to be conscious of the triggers that set you off and that no longer serve you as a mindful parent.

contents.name: Day 5 - Mindful Listening
contents.title: Day 5 - Mindful Listening
contents.description: In Day Five of the series, we look at the great importance of developing your skill as a mindful listener. Being present to the conversations you have with your children is vital for building respect and trust.

contents.name: Day 6 - Fostering Healthy Boundaries
contents.title: Day 6 - Fostering Healthy Boundaries
contents.description: In today's meditation we explore the need to set healthy boundaries with your family. We will touch on the themes of unconditional love and the role of the parent in modeling appropriate behavior.

contents.name: Day 7 - Self Compassion
contents.title: Day 7 - Self Compassion
contents.description: As we wrap up the series, we take the time to remember that parenting is hard and we're all doing the best we can. Self-compassion is mandatory. Warts and all.

contents.name: Day 1 - Intention
contents.title: Day 1 - Intention
contents.description:
Aging is a natural part of our evolution that can sometimes be rather challenging. So this 7 day series is designed to help you accept and embrace your natural aging process with poise and confidence.

Day 1 – In today's meditation you will explore the idea of living your life with intention and ask yourself some of the deeper 'soul' questions of life.

contents.name: Day 2 - The Present Moment
contents.title: Day 2 - The Present Moment
contents.description: When we fully and totally recognize that our time is precious and limited, we develop a deeper sense of appreciation for life. Life is truly a gift and today let's connect with the treasure that is the present moment.

contents.name: Day 3 - Impermanence
contents.title: Day 3 - Impermanence
contents.description: It's said that the only constant in life is change. And when we resist this, we resist life itself.  So instead, let's embrace the ever-evolving nature of the universe and find the beauty in impermanence.

contents.name: Day 4 - Letting Go
contents.title: Day 4 - Letting Go
contents.description: The more we are able to let go of our need to control life and its outcomes, the better we can embrace it with joy and acceptance. Let's explore this together in today's meditation.

contents.name: Day 5 - Allowing
contents.title: Day 5 - Allowing
contents.description: Life is a path with many twists and turns, and we don't always know what is around the corner. But when we allow it to unfold as it will, we can be greeted with unforeseen adventures and opportunities to learn.

contents.name: Day 6 - Who Am I?
contents.title: Day 6 - Who Am I?
contents.description: How you think about who you really are will strongly affect how you relate to the aging process. So in today's meditation, we'll look behind the curtain of identity to find your pure essence.

contents.name: Day 7 - Loving Kindness and Self Compassion
contents.title: Day 7 - Loving Kindness and Self Compassion
contents.description: As we close out our series on aging, we'll look at some of the deeper lessons of life and what they can teach us about aging gracefully. And finally, we'll take a meditation on loving kindness together and remember that all life is precious.
contents.short_title: Day 7 - Loving Kindness and Self Compassion

contents.name: Day 1 - Setting your Intention
contents.title: Day 1 - Setting your Intention
contents.description:
This 7 day series is designed to help you improve your ability to listen so you can connect on a deeper with the people in your life.

Day 1 – In today's meditation you will get in touch with your intention for starting this series and explore the qualities of a good listener.

contents.name: Day 2 - Being Present in the Moment
contents.title: Day 2 - Being Present in the Moment
contents.description: To fully and completely listen, we need to be present in the moment, not in our heads thinking about the future or the past. In today's meditation you'll connect with the present moment and practice giving your full attention.
contents.short_title: Day 2 - Being Present in the Moment

contents.name: Day 3 - Inner Presence
contents.title: Day 3 - Inner Presence
contents.description: In Day 3, you'll ask yourself some of the deeper questions of life and learn to listen to your inner voice and intuition.

contents.name: Day 4 - Barriers to True Listening
contents.title: Day 4 - Barriers to True Listening
contents.description: In today's meditation you'll explore the barriers and obstacles that prevent you from listening with your full and purposeful intent.

contents.name: Day 5 - The Shame Blame Game
contents.title: Day 5 - The Shame Blame Game
contents.description: Another obstacle to true listening is judgment. Let's explore this theme and discover how it prevents you from showing up and being present for a conversation.

contents.name: Day 6 - Meeting with an Open Heart
contents.title: Day 6 - Meeting with an Open Heart
contents.description: An open heart allows for respect and healing and a deeper level of sharing. Let's tune into this together today and practice a higher level of listening.
contents.short_title: Day 6 - Meeting with an Open Heart

contents.name: Day 7 - Putting It All Together
contents.title: Day 7 - Putting It All Together
contents.description: In our final meditation for the series, we'll tie together everything that we have learned, and explore the three steps to true listening.

contents.name: Day 1 - Getting Started
contents.title: Day 1 - Getting Started
contents.description:
Week 1: The 7 Day Challenge - Learn the Basics

In this first week of the daily program, we learn the basics and help build the foundation of a successful meditation practice. Relax and enjoy these daily, short guided meditations as you learn how simple and relaxing meditation can be.

Day 1 - When you're first learning to meditate, it's important to know that you don't need any special talent or abilities. You just have to get used to it, like any other skill. And this comes from practice. So in this meditation, you'll learn how to watch your breath and enjoy some relaxation from stress.

contents.name: Day 2 - Like Riding a Bike
contents.title: Day 2 - Like Riding a Bike
contents.description: This meditation picks up where Day 1 left off. You'll continue to practice the basics of meditation so they become like second nature to you.

contents.name: Day 3 - Right Expectations
contents.title: Day 3 - Right Expectations
contents.description: As you progress in learning meditation, it's natural to wonder if you're doing it right. It's a very normal question that comes up all the time. In this meditation, you'll continue to practice and learn to let go of any expectations you have about the outcomes of your meditations.

contents.name: Day 4 - Setting Intention
contents.title: Day 4 - Setting Intention
contents.description: Understanding and getting in touch with your intentions is a big theme when it comes to meditation. So in this meditation, you'll explore what those intentions are, so you can make sure you bring them into your life.

contents.name: Day 5 - Don't Try Too Hard
contents.title: Day 5 - Don't Try Too Hard
contents.description: As you learn to meditate, you might wonder how hard you should be trying. Another normal question. This meditation will answer this for you and help you find just the right balance for your practice.

contents.name: Day 6 - Feeling the Body
contents.title: Day 6 - Feeling the Body
contents.description: It's not just your mind that relaxes when you meditate, but your body too. So in this meditation, you'll learn to pay more attention to the physical sensations in your body and become aware of how you respond to them.

contents.name: Day 7 - Keeping the Peace
contents.title: Day 7 - Keeping the Peace
contents.description: In this meditation, we remember that the purpose of our practice is not to try to actively create a state of happiness. The aim is to take a step back from our busy minds and allow that sense of peace and tranquility to arise on its own.

contents.name: Keep Practicing
contents.title: Keep Practicing
contents.description:
If you've completed the first week of the Program using the free version, you can use this meditation as a daily practice to strengthen the basics of meditation. 

Premium users will be able to continue on to the next week and progress in learning new meditation skills.

contents.name: Day 1 - Your Busy Mind
contents.title: Day 1 - Your Busy Mind
contents.description:
Week 2: Yes! You Are Normal - Find the Meditation Groove

This week, we settle into the meditation groove and show you how to stay on track with your practice, and stay calm even when your mind is really busy.

Day 1 - As one starts a meditation practice, it's not long before they realize their mind just doesn't come with an off switch. Meditation helps us take back the controls, so to speak. In this meditation, you'll learn how to start building your 'attention muscle'.

contents.name: Day 2 - Finding the Time
contents.title: Day 2 - Finding the Time
contents.description: Finding the right time and place to meditate can sometimes be a challenge when you're first starting. We'll go into this subject a little deeper, and encourage you to think of meditation as something you can do anytime, anywhere.

contents.name: Day 3 - Staying Alert
contents.title: Day 3 - Staying Alert
contents.description: Finding the balance between staying relaxed but still alert enough not to fall asleep can sometimes be tricky. This meditation will help you figure out what's best for you.

contents.name: Day 4 - Relaxing Your Body
contents.title: Day 4 - Relaxing Your Body
contents.description: Our lives are usually so busy that when we take time to slow it all down and be still, we can sometimes feel bored or restless. This meditation will help you learn to cope with these responses and will continue to help you strengthen your attention muscle.

contents.name: Day 5 - Settling Your Mind
contents.title: Day 5 - Settling Your Mind
contents.description: Meditation tends to magnify whatever feelings you may be having, which can be a little startling at first. But this is a normal part of the process as your busy mind calms down. This meditation goes deeper into this common challenge.

contents.name: Day 6 - Dropping Judgment
contents.title: Day 6 - Dropping Judgment
contents.description: Meditation is simply about observing whatever it is that’s going on, so there's no need to judge whether you're doing it right or wrongly. But this is a common concern when we begin, so we'll touch on this subject in more detail in this meditation.

contents.name: Day 7 - Finding Your Groove
contents.title: Day 7 - Finding Your Groove
contents.description: The effects of meditation are gradual and tend to sneak up you, making it hard to notice anything from one day to the next. But they will come as long as you keep building the habit. This meditation will tie together what was learned this week and leave you with the encouragement to continue.

contents.name: Day 1 - Power of Attention
contents.title: Day 1 - Power of Attention
contents.description:
Week 3: The Attention Muscle - Find Calm & Clarity. Anytime.

In this third week of the daily program, we continue to practice stepping back from our busy minds and learning to experience the calm and clarity of the present moment.

Day 1 - When we meditate, we exercise our 'attention muscle'. This means we learn to better control how and where we direct our mind’s attention. We'll explore this topic further and introduce a mindfulness practice as well.

contents.name: Day 2 - Mind-Full-Ness?
contents.title: Day 2 - Mind-Full-Ness?
contents.description: In this meditation, we'll explore the topic of mind-ful-ness in greater detail. Think of it as the opposite of mind-less-ness. With mindfulness, we aim to be present to the moments as they happen, not oblivious.

contents.name: Day 3 - Being in the Moment
contents.title: Day 3 - Being in the Moment
contents.description: Day 3 picks up right where we left on Day 2 to bring an even greater sense of mindfulness into your meditation. We'll also spend time exploring the many benefits of building your attention muscle.

contents.name: Day 4 - Opening the Lens
contents.title: Day 4 - Opening the Lens
contents.description: This meditation explores the difference between an exercise in concentration, like focusing on your breath, and general attentiveness, which is what we do in a mindfulness practice.

contents.name: Day 5 - Watching Thoughts
contents.title: Day 5 - Watching Thoughts
contents.description: It's tempting to think that we should be trying to get rid of our thoughts when we meditate, but we couldn't do that even if we tried. Trying to stop thinking just creates more thinking. In this meditation, we explore the connection between our thoughts and our attention in greater detail.

contents.name: Day 6 - Accepting Thoughts
contents.title: Day 6 - Accepting Thoughts
contents.description: Meditation is about acceptance, not resistance. In this meditation we'll practice accepting whatever it is that's happening in the present moment. The good, the bad, and the ugly. And that includes your thoughts.

contents.name: Day 7 - The Here and Now
contents.title: Day 7 - The Here and Now
contents.description: This week has been an exploration of mindfulness and we continue in this meditation with a look at what is called, 'Choiceless Awareness'.

contents.name: Day 1 - The Present Moment
contents.title: Day 1 - The Present Moment
contents.description:
Week 4: Are You Where Your Body Is? - Bring Your Mind and Body Together

This week, we focus on our body sensations and see how to use them as an anchor to the present moment. You'll also learn some simple tips to start bringing a bit more peace into your daily life, no matter what's going on.

Day 1 – This meditation sets the tone for Week 4 where we deepen your connection between your physical presence and your mental attention. When you're truly present in the moment, you experience the peace and stillness that are the gifts of meditation.

contents.name: Day 2 - What's Happening
contents.title: Day 2 - What's Happening
contents.description: When you are in the 'here and now', you are focused on what is actually happening in the present moment. And in that moment, you're not thinking about what has happened or what might happen, you're aware and engaged. This meditation furthers your practice of being present in the moment and strengthening your attention muscle.

contents.name: Day 3 - Like a Newborn Baby
contents.title: Day 3 - Like a Newborn Baby
contents.description: For many of us, our attention is so fragmented that we are rarely in the present moment, rarely still. This meditation is a practice in bringing a newborn baby's sense of sheer moment to moment presence into your life.

contents.name: Day 4 - Finding the Gaps
contents.title: Day 4 - Finding the Gaps
contents.description: For some reason, the mind doesn't naturally turn itself off when it's not needed. But, as you turn up the volume of the present moment, you turn down the volume of stressful mind activity. This meditation seeks to do just that.

contents.name: Day 5 - Presence in Between
contents.title: Day 5 - Presence in Between
contents.description: This meditation builds on our awareness of the gaps between your thoughts and the gaps at the beginning and end of each breath. By paying special attention to these pauses, we connect with the present moment on a deeper level.

contents.name: Day 6 - The Waiting Game
contents.title: Day 6 - The Waiting Game
contents.description: There's a phenomenon I call, "trying to go faster than the speed of life." This is when we find ourselves wanting to get to the next moment faster than life is allowing. This meditation will help you take notice of this mental state and encourage you to be present in those moments instead.

contents.name: Day 7 - Cutting Your Losses
contents.title: Day 7 - Cutting Your Losses
contents.description: In this meditation, we explore two magic words… "It's OK." You can use these as a trigger to remind yourself not to go down any negative paths in your mind, and to come back to the present moment instead.

contents.name: Day 1 - Being One With All
contents.title: Day 1 - Being One With All
contents.description:
Week 12: Making the Connection - From Me to We

As your mind chatter naturally lessens, the light of presence in you grows. Much like the sun's rays peeking in thru breaks in the clouds. This week, we'll explore how this expands our feelings of connectedness – to others, to the world around us, and to our authentic selves.

Day 1 – This meditation seeks to expand upon our understandings of 'perspective'. You'll take a step back and explore how your meditation practice can heighten your sense of connectedness to include the various elements of your environment.

contents.name: Day 2 - Connecting With Empathy
contents.title: Day 2 - Connecting With Empathy
contents.description: Continuing with our exploration on the theme of connection, we look at the ways in which you are connected to the people in your life on an emotional level. This makes it easier to understand how and why people behave the way they do.

contents.name: Day 3 - Feeling the Energy
contents.title: Day 3 - Feeling the Energy
contents.description: We're all connected to everyone and everything through energy.  Your meditation practice helps you tap into that energy, and begin to sense it more and more.  In this meditation, you'll expand this emotional connection with others and open the door to a wellspring of creativity, intuition and wisdom.

contents.name: Day 4 - Opening the Channel
contents.title: Day 4 - Opening the Channel
contents.description: Picking up where we left off last time, in this meditation you'll cultivate a warm, open, and positive vibe so that you will attract the same quality of energy into your life.

contents.name: Day 5 - Our Authentic Self
contents.title: Day 5 - Our Authentic Self
contents.description: As we connect to ourselves more authentically, we begin to notice those little signs that tell us when we're disconnected from the stuff that really matters to us. Getting in touch with, and honoring your deeper self, is the aim of this meditation.

contents.name: Day 6 - The Life Force Within
contents.title: Day 6 - The Life Force Within
contents.description: Your authentic self is the source of your creativity, your wisdom and your intuition.  It is the wellspring of calm and clarity and love.  The more we can connect to this source, the more we experience these qualities in our life.  And this is the heart of why we meditate.

contents.name: Day 7 - The Divine in Us
contents.title: Day 7 - The Divine in Us
contents.description: In this meditation, we aim to connect with that divine spark that resides in each and every one of us.  To quiet our minds and feel a sense of oneness with all beings.

contents.name: Day 1 - Your Inner Movie
contents.title: Day 1 - Your Inner Movie
contents.description:
Week 6: Taming of the Mind - Our Personal Movie

This week, we look at our thoughts and emotions using the metaphor of 'making a movie'. You will see how shifting our perspective from being the star of our personal movie to being simply the camera person can take us out of our stress and anxiety.

Day 1 – In this meditation, we use the metaphor of 'Making the Movie' to illustrate the different roles we play in the unfolding of our own inner lives.

contents.name: Day 2 - Yums and Yucks
contents.title: Day 2 - Yums and Yucks
contents.description: We continue our gentle exploration of the inner world and the labels we sometimes attach to our experiences. And we also continue to bring a sense of peace and calmness into your life.

contents.name: Day 3 - The Cameraman
contents.title: Day 3 - The Cameraman
contents.description: As you get to know your mind a bit better, you can come to see more clearly what's getting in the way of a sense of peace. We'll explore this in today's meditation and continue to grow your awareness to the workings of your mind.

contents.name: Day 4 - Resisting Resistance
contents.title: Day 4 - Resisting Resistance
contents.description: We all have the tendency to avoid or resist the things we don't like and cling to the things that give us pleasure. It's a pretty normal response to daily life. But in this meditation we look to shift from resistance to acceptance, as this can be one of the most powerful changes you can make to bring more peace and happiness into your life.

contents.name: Day 5 - Just Observing...
contents.title: Day 5 - Just Observing...
contents.description: The more you train yourself to step back and observe your thinking mind, over and over, as we do when we meditate, the stronger your attention muscle gets. In this meditation, we continue to recognize your patterns of thinking and how to get past the ones that cause you stress.

contents.name: Day 6 - Accepting it All
contents.title: Day 6 - Accepting it All
contents.description: In this meditation we go further into understanding what is meant by 'letting go of resistance'. It's a very real way of bringing a bit more peace, and happiness into your life, and who doesn't want that? :)

contents.name: Day 7 - Nothing to Do
contents.title: Day 7 - Nothing to Do
contents.description: As we explore these topics, it's important to remember that meditation is a time to relax your busy mind, and let go of any sense of effort. This meditation ties together the themes we have explored throughout the week and will leave you more focused and less stressed.

contents.name: Day 1 - Letting Go of Control
contents.title: Day 1 - Letting Go of Control
contents.description:
Week 7: Letting Go of the Mind - Letting Go of the Reins

As you develop your meditation practice, you begin to notice how much mental energy is about 'staying in control'. This week, we focus on letting go a bit and noticing when you're not fully accepting the present moments.

Day 1 - It's really important to keep in mind that accepting what’s happening doesn't mean liking it, or even wanting it, choosing it, or supporting it. It just means not resisting it. In this meditation we explore this important concept and learn to liberate ourselves from being constantly upset and disappointed by life.

contents.name: Day 2 - Power Thru Acceptance
contents.title: Day 2 - Power Thru Acceptance
contents.description: As we all know, we really have very little control over the world, or the people, around us. So the more you can practice acceptance in your life, the less stress you’ll have, and the happier you’ll be. This is what we practice in this meditation as we train ourselves to be less reactive.

contents.name: Day 3 - Looking Inside
contents.title: Day 3 - Looking Inside
contents.description: Our days are filled with situations and interactions where your experience is the result of your own perception. This meditation will help you turn your attention inward, so you can begin to realize that all the change you want to see in your life comes from within you.

contents.name: Day 4 - Your Frame of Mind
contents.title: Day 4 - Your Frame of Mind
contents.description: Getting to a place of peace and clarity, and a place of happiness, is about looking inside ourselves, not outside. And that's exactly why we meditate. And over time, that sense of calm acceptance we practice in meditation starts to pervade our lives. We will practice this understanding in today's meditation.

contents.name: Day 5 - Accepting Change
contents.title: Day 5 - Accepting Change
contents.description: In this meditation, we explore the nature of change and impermanence in life and how to approach it from a place of acceptance, rather than resistance.

contents.name: Day 6  - Fake It til You Make It
contents.title: Day 6  - Fake It til You Make It
contents.description: It takes a bit of time and effort to change habits and reactions, so in this meditation we continue to make clear what is meant by acceptance. We work on letting go of negative mental energy and the resistance we create in our minds.
contents.short_title: Day 6  - Fake It til You Make It

contents.name: Day 7 - Embracing Change
contents.title: Day 7 - Embracing Change
contents.description: In the final meditation for this week, you learn to embrace the curveballs that life throws at you, and to let go of trying to make the world fit your own personal plans. Life just doesn't work that way and you'll stress a lot less when you let go.

contents.name: Day 1 - Reactive Patterns
contents.title: Day 1 - Reactive Patterns
contents.description:
Week 8: What's on Your Playlist? - Breaking the Reactivity Cycle

Did you know the average person has 40-60,000 thoughts per day going through their minds? And most of them are the same ones as the day before. This week, we focus on those repetitive 'sticky' thoughts and feelings – especially the ones that cause you to react in ways that don't serve you.

Day 1 – When we quiet our minds, we start to see the patterns that can cause us to react unconsciously to the situations in our life. In this meditation, you will continue to develop the skill of simply noticing your thoughts, and learn how to create space so you can then actively choose how you want to respond.

contents.name: Day 2 - Over and Over Again
contents.title: Day 2 - Over and Over Again
contents.description: As you slow down and take the time to pay attention to what’s going on around you, and within you, you can start to observe things with a bit more clarity.  In this meditation, we will spend the time becoming aware of the habitual thoughts and actions in your life so you can cultivate the good ones and discard those that don't serve you.

contents.name: Day 3 - Creating Your Reality
contents.title: Day 3 - Creating Your Reality
contents.description: How you see the world has very real consequences for your happiness.  This is why it is so important to be aware of the patterns of thought that you house in your mind.  In this meditation, you will continue to practice your powers of observation in order to detect the thoughts that can cause you stress and anxiety.

contents.name: Day 4 - Curiosity
contents.title: Day 4 - Curiosity
contents.description: One of the great benefits of meditation is that it naturally makes us more curious about the world around us. We learn to step back and observe, and we become more perceptive and sensitive. Just like we were when we were kids. Today we aim to bring more curiosity into your meditation so you can learn more about yourself and how you tick.

contents.name: Day 5 - Powerful Thoughts
contents.title: Day 5 - Powerful Thoughts
contents.description: The thoughts you have can trigger all kinds of reactions, from stress and anger to bliss and happiness.  That's why becoming familiar with your 'playlist' of thoughts is the first step on the road to increased peace and tranquility.  This meditation picks up where we left off last time as we continue to notice what types of thoughts and feelings come up for you.

contents.name: Day 6 - Whose Playlist Is It?
contents.title: Day 6 - Whose Playlist Is It?
contents.description: Everyone has their own playlist of thoughts. You know … those repetitive patterns of thinking that can trigger instinctive reactions in us. But we also take on playlists from other people, such as our parents and friends. Kind of like having an iPod full of someone else's favorite tunes. In this meditation, we will continue to bring awareness to your thoughts, feelings and reactions to help you see when you're dancing to someone else's tune.

contents.name: Day 7 - Automatic Triggers
contents.title: Day 7 - Automatic Triggers
contents.description: We all tend to react, and often over-react, to thoughts that trigger emotional responses.  The stronger your reactions, both on the positive and negative sides, the more you should pay attention.  In this meditation, we'll continue to develop your awareness so you can make choices that lead to more peace and less stress.

contents.name: Day 1 - Creating Abundance
contents.title: Day 1 - Creating Abundance
contents.description:
Week 9: Seeds of Abundance - Abundance Is the Present

We can have everything we want in each moment  as long as we don't want anything to be different from the way it is. This week, we meditate with a focus on finding full acceptance for the 'here and now', and we'll explore how that can shift your perspective from lack to abundance.

Day 1 – Abundance can mean many different things to many people. At its core, abundance is more a state of mind than the things it represents. In this meditation, we'll take some time to observe whether your thoughts and feelings tend to be focused on appreciating the things you do have rather than on what you don't have.

contents.name: Day 2 - Attitude of Gratitude
contents.title: Day 2 - Attitude of Gratitude
contents.description: This meditation picks up where we left off on Day 1 as we continue to explore the intimate connection between feelings of abundance and expressions of gratitude.

contents.name: Day 3 - Appreciation
contents.title: Day 3 - Appreciation
contents.description: Did you know that practicing gratitude has been proven to increase your energy, your self-esteem, your social connections, and your overall happiness?  For these reasons, we continue to explore this important topic in today's meditation.

contents.name: Day 4 - The Happiness State
contents.title: Day 4 - The Happiness State
contents.description: Being happy and at peace is actually our natural state … it just gets obscured by our busy minds. Just as the sun is always there, even when the sky is covered with clouds. In this meditation, we'll disburse those clouds by stepping back from our thoughts and appreciating the present moment.

contents.name: Day 5 - The Next Next Thing
contents.title: Day 5 - The Next Next Thing
contents.description: Appreciating what we have in the present moment, and being grateful for the simple things is a key to lasting happiness.  In this meditation, we'll continue to take the time to focus your attention on 'What's Now'.

contents.name: Day 6 - Abundance Is Now
contents.title: Day 6 - Abundance Is Now
contents.description: Through meditation, we keep our sense of appreciation and wonder for life.  In this meditation, we'll nurture that spark of child-like curiosity that will make you happier and keep you feeling young.

contents.name: Day 7 - The Silver Lining
contents.title: Day 7 - The Silver Lining
contents.description: No matter what may be going on in your life, there is always something to be grateful for. In fact, being grateful can help you alleviate some of the pain you may be experiencing. In this meditation, we'll remember that abundance is about how you feel – a way of being – not a pot of gold at the end of some imaginary rainbow.

contents.name: Day 1 - The Illusion of Reality
contents.title: Day 1 - The Illusion of Reality
contents.description:
Week 10: Perspectives - Seeing the Big Picture

As stepping back from your thoughts becomes more natural for you, your perspective begins to get wider, and you begin to rise above your own 'me-centered' story line. This naturally opens you up to other points of view. This week, we'll explore how this feeds your sense of compassion and empathy, both for yourselves and for others.

Day 1 – We all naturally see things from our own perspective. And when we develop the ability to see things from other people's points of view, we are then able to reduce the conflict in our lives. Meditation helps us create this space to do just that and this is the focus in today's meditation.

contents.name: Day 2 - Our Hot Buttons
contents.title: Day 2 - Our Hot Buttons
contents.description: Putting yourself in someone else's shoes is easier when you're calm and less stressed. Likewise, connecting with your empathy is more difficult when one of your hot buttons is being pushed. In this meditation, you'll continue to practice noticing your emotions with a sense of detachment, and without judgment, so you can become more attuned with yourself.

contents.name: Day 3 - Who Am I?
contents.title: Day 3 - Who Am I?
contents.description: In this meditation, we continue to explore the importance of expanding your awareness of other people's perspectives. The goal is to be more present and connected as a human being, and the benefit is that this will bring more happiness into your life.

contents.name: Day 4 - Our Natural Empathy
contents.title: Day 4 - Our Natural Empathy
contents.description: The judgments that we make about the people we see or the experiences we have, can prevent us from connecting with our natural sense of empathy. In this meditation, you'll practice putting your awareness on this sense of judgment, so you can let go of it, and open the door to being more accepting to the people around you.

contents.name: Day 5 - More Than Meets the Eye
contents.title: Day 5 - More Than Meets the Eye
contents.description: Developing our sense of compassion and empathy can sometimes be difficult.  Especially when someone is so very different from us.  In today's meditation, you'll continue to develop the awareness that there is often more than meets the eye in life, and everyone has their own story that makes them who they are.
contents.short_title: Day 5 - More Than Meets the Eye

contents.name: Day 6 - Filling Our Bucket
contents.title: Day 6 - Filling Our Bucket
contents.description: It's important to remember we can only really generate compassion and empathy when we are feeling good ourselves.  If your bucket of love is full, then you will have enough to share.  In this meditation, you'll focus on finding a sense of love and compassion for the most important person in your life – Yourself.

contents.name: Day 7 - Stepping Back
contents.title: Day 7 - Stepping Back
contents.description: In the final meditation for this week, you'll continue to grow your perspective and sense of empathy as you build the foundation to deal with life in a more harmonious and less stressful way.

contents.name: Day 1 - The Gift of Presence
contents.title: Day 1 - The Gift of Presence
contents.description:
Week 11: Playing Well with Others - Relationships Are Our Teacher

For many of us, our relationships are the source of much of our stress and anxiety. The people closest to us tend to be the biggest triggers of our reactivity. This week, we'll look at how your meditation practice can help you slow this process down in the heat of the moment, giving you the opportunity to react consciously, rather than automatically. 

Day 1 – In this meditation, you'll work on developing the skill of being truly present for those around you. This means honestly and genuinely listening to what they have to share, and giving them your full attention so you can improve the interactions and relationships in your life.

contents.name: Day 2 - Watching Judgment
contents.title: Day 2 - Watching Judgment
contents.description: When you start to relate to the people in your life with less judgment and let go of the negative mental energy that it creates, you can enjoy more harmonious, compassionate and meaningful relationships.  That's what today's meditation is all about.

contents.name: Day 3 - Relationship Playlists
contents.title: Day 3 - Relationship Playlists
contents.description: Our relationships can have a huge effect on our level of happiness.  So as you become more in tune with the present moment you can begin to deal with people consciously, with self-awareness, and a sense of personal responsibility.  This simple shift can open the door to a new-found sense of personal power that can bring joy and harmony into your relationships.

contents.name: Day 4 - People Who Love People
contents.title: Day 4 - People Who Love People
contents.description: When we meditate, we’re practicing acceptance.  And there’s no better place than our relationships to practice this in our daily lives.  In this meditation, you'll focus on accepting people as they are, in their full imperfection, in order to find more peace in your life.

contents.name: Day 5 - Conflict Re-framed
contents.title: Day 5 - Conflict Re-framed
contents.description: In today's meditation, we go one step beyond acceptance into actual appreciation.  This can sometimes be difficult, but the rewards are connecting to people at a deeper level, and seeing them with more empathy and compassion.

contents.name: Day 6 - It's Not Personal
contents.title: Day 6 - It's Not Personal
contents.description: The power in observing your thoughts, is that it separates you from them just a wee bit.  This space of separation is what then allows you to take things less personally.  In relationships, this doesn’t mean not caring, or becoming emotionally distant, it means recognizing that not everything is about us.  Let's explore this topic further in today's meditation.

contents.name: Day 7 - The Assumption Trap
contents.title: Day 7 - The Assumption Trap
contents.description: This meditation picks up where we left off last time and explores the ways in which our own personal interpretations and perceptions can cause conflict in our relationships.

contents.name: Day 1 - Thoughts & Feelings
contents.title: Day 1 - Thoughts & Feelings
contents.description:
Week 5: Meeting of the Mind - Getting to Know Your Mind

As we continue to practice coming back to our breath when our minds get really busy, this week, we begin to take note of what type of thoughts and emotions keep coming up for you, and how they feel in your body. This new awareness gives us the opportunity to change our reactions.

Day 1 – In this meditation we focus on taking a step back so you can better take notice of your thoughts. Every time you do this, you're taking a step forward toward a happier, less reactive and more peaceful life.

contents.name: Day 2 - Emotional Energy
contents.title: Day 2 - Emotional Energy
contents.description: Today we will build on our understanding of the difference between thoughts and emotions. This meditation will help you learn to notice which thoughts and feelings may have a bit of an emotional charge that comes with them.

contents.name: Day 3 - Workings of the Mind
contents.title: Day 3 - Workings of the Mind
contents.description: In this meditation, we continue our exploration of the world of feelings and how our minds actually work. By observing what's going on in your mind, you can come to have a better understanding of yourself.

contents.name: Day 4 - Sticky Feelings
contents.title: Day 4 - Sticky Feelings
contents.description: Have you noticed how some thoughts come and go rather quickly and some tend to stick around? In this meditation we dig a little deeper into the differences between thoughts and feelings.

contents.name: Day 5 - Watching the Signs
contents.title: Day 5 - Watching the Signs
contents.description: Imagine driving a car without being able to see any of the gauges. You'd be driving blind. Our feelings serve pretty much the same purpose in our lives, and in this meditation we continue to get in touch with the truth of our inner state.

contents.name: Day 6 - Difficult Feelings
contents.title: Day 6 - Difficult Feelings
contents.description: In today's meditation, we take a look at how to handle the unpleasant spectrum of emotions and continue to examine the mind you've lived with all your life.

contents.name: Day 7 - Feelings & Sensations
contents.title: Day 7 - Feelings & Sensations
contents.description: Our bodies are continuously giving us clues and as we continue to learn how to listen to them, we deepen our understanding of the thoughts and emotions that make up our inner world.

contents.name: Better Sleep
contents.title: Better Sleep
contents.description:
Better Sleep Series

Take Your Meditation to Bed

In this 7 day series, we explore how your meditation practice can help you enjoy better nights' sleep.  Using the same techniques from your meditation practice, you'll learn how to develop better 'sleep hygiene', and to counteract the anxious thinking that keeps many of us up at night.

contents.name: Stress Less!
contents.title: Stress Less!
contents.description:
Stress Less! Series

Don't Stress About it.

This week, we put stress under the microscope. We'll explore the nature and sources of much of our stress, and you'll see how much of it you actually have some control over. We'll explore how you can lessen your stress thru simple meditation techniques.

contents.name: Feeling Happier
contents.title: Feeling Happier
contents.description:
Feeling Happier Series

Melt Away Those Blues

Enjoy these 7 daily, guided meditations focused on getting in touch with what truly makes you happy. Learn how the practice of presence - both in meditation and in daily life - can be the doorway to new-found happiness.

contents.name: Relationship Harmony
contents.title: Relationship Harmony
contents.description:
Relationship Harmony Series

Getting to the Root of Conflict

This week, we'll look at how the skills we learned in meditation can help you deal better with relationship conflict and bring more harmony into your life. Focusing on self-awareness, we'll look at how our automatic reactions can be replaced with calm conscious actions.

contents.name: Mindfulness & Social Media
contents.title: Mindfulness & Social Media
contents.description:
Mindfulness & Social Media Series

Using Technology Mindfully

Technology and social media are here to stay, and are becoming an increasingly important part of our lives. This week, you'll enjoy relaxing guided meditations focused on using these tools in a balanced and mindful way.

contents.name: Weight Loss
contents.title: Weight Loss
contents.description:
Weight Loss Series

A New Approach to Losing Weight

This week, we'll explore how feelings and emotions lie at the root of our eating habits. These relaxing guided meditations will give you a new perspective about your motivations, as well as some great tips to bring mindfulness into your relationship with food.

contents.name: Getting What You Want
contents.title: Getting What You Want
contents.description:
Getting What You Want Series

Our Deepest Desires

Many people don't get what they want simply because they don't know what they're looking for. This week, you'll get in touch with what it is you desire at your deepest levels and find that it may be closer than you know.

contents.name: Letting Go
contents.title: Letting Go
contents.description: It's interesting to see how the more we resist life events the more stress we actually feel. It appears counter-intuitive, but yet the only thing we can control in our lives are our own reactions. We often resist things that have already happened, or live in fear of what may happen. And that keeps us stuck holding on to what might have been or what we hope might be. This week we'll spend time recognizing 'what is' and we'll practice the art of letting go. The more we practice this, the more vibrant and alive we feel. So let's get started.

contents.name: Overcoming Addiction
contents.title: Overcoming Addiction
contents.description:
For most of us, quitting an addiction and changing our habits can be a huge challenge.  

This 7 day series is meant to support you by bringing awareness to your underlying beliefs so that you can then influence your unconscious mind and unleash yourself.

contents.name: Mindful Parenting
contents.title: Mindful Parenting
contents.description: Parenting is one of the greatest challenges we can undertake in this life. So this 7 day series is meant to support your growth as a parent to foster more mindfulness, understanding and compassion.

contents.name: Aging
contents.title: Aging
contents.description: Aging is a natural part of our evolution that can sometimes be rather challenging. So this 7 day series is designed to help you accept and embrace your natural aging process with poise and confidence.

contents.name: Themed Weeks
contents.title: Themed Weeks
contents.description: A collection of themed 7 day series focusing on life challenges and the most important benefits of meditation.

contents.name: Specialty
contents.title: Life Situations
contents.description: Guided meditations and visualizations for many life situations and challenges.

contents.name: Kids
contents.title: Kids & Family
contents.description: Guided meditations for the family, including young kids, tweens and teens.

contents.name: SelfPractice
contents.title: Less Guidance
contents.description: Meditations with less formal guidance. These feature a few occasional reminders blended with music, nature sounds or silence.

contents.name: BedtimeStories
contents.title: Bedtime Stories
contents.description: Relax your mind and allow sleep to come take you away with this selection of bedtime stories read to you in a soothing and peaceful tone.

contents.name: LearnToMeditateW1
contents.title: W1: The 7 Day Challenge
contents.description:
Week 1: The 7 Day Challenge

Learn the Basics

In this first week of the daily program, we learn the basics and help build the foundation of a successful meditation practice. Relax and enjoy these daily, short guided meditations as you learn how simple and relaxing meditation can be.

contents.name: LearnToMeditateW3
contents.title: W3: The Attention Muscle
contents.description:
Week 3: The Attention Muscle

Find Calm & Clarity. Anytime.

In this third week of the daily program, we continue to practice stepping back from our busy minds and learning to experience the calm and clarity of the present moment.

contents.name: LearnToMeditateW2
contents.title: W2: Yes! You Are Normal
contents.description:
Week 2: Yes! You Are Normal

Find the Meditation Groove

This week, we settle into the meditation groove and show you how to stay on track with your practice, and stay calm even when your mind is really busy.

contents.name: LearnToMeditateW4
contents.title: W4: Are You Where Your Body Is?
contents.description:
Week 4: Are You Where Your Body Is?

Bring Your Mind and Body Together

This week, we focus on our body sensations and see how to use them as an anchor to the present moment. You'll also learn some simple tips to start bringing a bit more peace into your daily life, no matter what's going on.

contents.name: LearnToMeditateW5
contents.title: W5: Meeting of the Mind
contents.description:
Week 5: Meeting of the Mind

Getting to Know Your Mind

As we continue to practice coming back to our breath when our minds get really busy, this week, we begin to take note of what type of thoughts and emotions keep coming up for you, and how they feel in your body. This new awareness gives us the opportunity to change our reactions.

contents.name: LearnToMeditateW6
contents.title: W6: Taming of the Mind
contents.description:
Week 6: Taming of the Mind

Our Personal Movie

This week, we look at our thoughts and emotions using the metaphor of 'making a movie'. You will see how shifting our perspective from being the star of our personal movie to being simply the camera person can take us out of our stress and anxiety.

contents.name: LearnToMeditateW7
contents.title: W7: Letting Go of the Mind
contents.description:
Week 7: Letting Go of the Mind

Letting Go of the Reins

As you develop your meditation practice, you begin to notice how much mental energy is about 'staying in control'. This week, we focus on letting go a bit and noticing when you're not fully accepting the present moments.

contents.name: LearnToMeditateW8
contents.title: W8: What's on Your Playlist?
contents.description:
Week 8: What's on Your Playlist?

Breaking the Reactivity Cycle

Did you know the average person has 40-60,000 thoughts per day going through their minds? And most of them are the same ones as the day before. This week, we focus on those repetitive 'sticky' thoughts and feelings - especially the ones that cause you to react in ways that don't serve you.

contents.name: LearnToMeditateW9
contents.title: W9: Seeds of Abundance
contents.description:
Week 9: Seeds of Abundance

Abundance Is the Present

We can have everything we want in each moment  as long as we don't want anything to be different from the way it is. This week, we meditate with a focus on finding full acceptance for the 'here and now', and we'll explore how that can shift your perspective from lack to abundance.

contents.name: LearnToMeditateW10
contents.title: W10: Perspectives
contents.description:
Week 10: Perspectives

Seeing the Big Picture

As stepping back from your thoughts becomes more natural for you, your perspective begins to get wider, and you begin to rise above your own 'me-centered' story line. This naturally opens you up to other points of view. This week, we'll explore how this feeds your sense of compassion and empathy, both for yourselves and for others.

contents.name: LearnToMeditateW11
contents.title: W11: Playing Well with Others
contents.description:
Week 11: Playing Well with Others

Relationships Are Our Teacher

For many of us, our relationships are the source of much of our stress and anxiety. The people closest to us tend to be the biggest triggers of our reactivity. This week, we'll look at how your meditation practice can help you slow this process down in the heat of the moment, giving you the opportunity to react consciously, rather than automatically.

contents.name: LearnToMeditateW12
contents.title: W12: Making the Connection
contents.description:
Week 12: Making the Connection

From Me to We

As your mind chatter naturally lessens, the light of presence in you grows. Much like the sun's rays peeking in thru breaks in the clouds. This week, we'll explore how this expands our feelings of connectedness - to others, to the world around us, and to our authentic selves.

contents.name: LearnToMeditate
contents.title: Learn to Meditation
contents.description: The most effective way to begin. A new meditation every day for 12 weeks to teach you everything you need to know.

authors.name: Jason Stephenson
authors.bio: View website Jason Stephenson is a music producer, vocalist, meditation guide and is the CEO of Relax Me Online Australia. His love of music has led him to work with various new age musicians worldwide to gather some of the best ambient new age music available. Please enjoy some of Jason's favorite relaxation tracks.

authors.name: Christopher Lloyd Clarke
authors.bio: View website Christopher is a composer who specializes in music for deep relaxation, healing and enhanced meditation. He has been making music and practicing meditation for over 20 years. From his studio in beautiful Apollo Bay on the southern coast of Australia, his ongoing mission is to create music that helps people live happier, healthier and more peaceful lives. Christopher has degrees in biological science and metaphysical science and has also trained in sound healing, energy healing and audio production. Christopher collaborates with professional therapists and healers around the world to create soothing music that helps their clients relax. His connection to this global network of professionals has given him a unique insight into how to create music that encourages deep relaxation, healing, spiritual awakening and other altered states of consciousness. Today, Christopher’s music is used by thousands of professional meditation teachers, hypnotherapists, psychologists and holistic healers. Luminaries such as Deepak Chopra, Oprah Winfrey, Neale Donald Walsch, Julian Lennon and others have all featured his music in their audio productions. Christopher absolutely loves making music. Christopher also enjoys surfing, spending time in nature, doing yoga and eating more cake than he should. Inner peace is one of his highest priorities, so he lives a particularly quiet life with plenty of time devoted to meditation and relaxation.

authors.name: Peter Kater
authors.bio: View website Grammy Winning/Multi-Platinum selling Pianist/Composer Peter Kater has been leading innovator of contemporary instrumental music for over 3 decades. He’s received many awards and accolades for his rich and diverse music including 13 Grammy Award nominations. A prolific composer, he’s released over 70 critically acclaimed recordings and has scored the music for over 100 television and film productions including 11 On & Off-Broadway dramatic plays. From solo piano and contemporary jazz ensembles to full orchestral works his music is heard all over the world crossing many genres from the Olympics, the Kennedy Center and Carnegie Hall to the treatment rooms of hundreds of thousands massage and healing practitioners. He is known for his many groundbreaking collaborations with musicians such as Native American flutist R. Carlos Nakai; Tibetan flutist Nawang Khechog; Sting guitarist Dominic Miller and Sacred Chantress Snatam Kaur. And as avid environmentalist and humanitarian Peter is a proud recipient of the Environment Leadership Award from the United Nations.

authors.name: Deuter
authors.bio: View website Born in postwar Germany, Deuter taught himself the guitar, the flute, harmonica and just about every instrument he could get his hands on, though it wasn’t until after a near-fatal car crash in his early twenties that he decided to pursue a career in music. His first release in 1970 marked the beginning of Deuter’s spiritual and musical journey, ostensibly paving the way for a new genre of music known as “New Age”, which combined acoustic and electronic elements with ethnic instrumentation and nature sounds, such as whale and bird songs, the open sea, and wind in the trees. Over the years, Deuter has continued to learn and master a vast array of instruments, including flutes, shakuhachi, guitar, banjo, sitar, santoor, piano, cello, tibetan bells, koto, bouzouki, keyboards, and viola da gamba. He’s recorded and released over 60 albums and has sold too many to count. All the while, Deuter has never ceased to explore new frequencies and resonances. “One thing that is important for me is that I love dancing on the edge of the unknown—to play around and open doors I haven’t walked through before”, says Deuter. It is this very outlook that has kept him at the forefront of musical evolution for over 40 years. Deuter currently lives and works in the mountains outside of Sante Fe, New Mexico, creating the contemplative, healing music he has become known for today.

authors.name: Lynne Goldberg
authors.bio:
How did a stressed-out, sleep-deprived, type-A businesswoman end up as a renowned meditation coach with a widely popular program teaching hundreds of thousands of people how to meditate?
 
When it comes to meditating, no one would have labeled Lynne Goldberg "a natural." After a series of devastating life blows including the loss of twin baby girls, her mother, her marriage, and her job, coupled with years of infertility treatment and multiple failed adoptions, she counted on copious amounts of work and wine to help her survive. But in the quiet moments she was forced to face the fact that, ultimately, she was still alone, unhappy, unfulfilled, and disconnected. Something—in fact, everything—was missing.
 
Dragged kicking and screaming by a friend to a yoga retreat, Lynne reluctantly abided by the meat-free, alcohol-free diet and sat through the meditations simply because there was nowhere else to go. But as she found her stress and anxiety slowly dissipating, the reluctance transformed into acceptance, and acceptance into appreciation and outright enjoyment. There was no denying the transformative effects this balanced, healthy approach was having on her life. She felt calm, capable, and in control.
 
Lynne course-corrected her life onto a path to understanding and embraced a new healthy and balanced lifestyle, studying along the way with Jon Kabat-Zinn, Deepak Chopra, Sri Dharma Mittra and Tony Robbins. Today she is an expert meditation coach, yoga instructor, strategic interventionist, and author of the book "Get Balanced. Get Blissed".
 
Her passion and life mission lie in helping others transform their lives and discover true happiness, peace of mind and fulfillment through meditation and personal growth. Her ability to compassionately connect with others, and her accessible, everyday approach to teaching meditation, have led her to coach people from all walks of life, from celebrities, athletes, and business executives to 80-year-old cancer patients and five-year-old children.  
 
Lynne's meditation programs and curriculum have been implemented in elementary and high schools, special needs schools, and hospitals.
 
When Lynne is not helping people find their bliss, she is living her own doing the things she loves most: being in nature, hiking or biking, traveling the world, cooking, or enjoying time with her husband and kids.

authors.name: Dr. Janette Freeman

As an author, speaker, teacher and coach, she assists the person in moving through previous subconscious blocks in order to live more from their Higher Self and experience greater health, success, happiness and inner peace. Her vision and mission are simply to manifest more 'Heaven on Earth', through a shift in consciousness individually and globally.

authors.name: Glenda Cedarleaf
authors.bio: View website Glenda Cedarleaf fell in love with creating meditation audios in 1994. Since then, she has combined meditative practices and guided imagery with specially chosen background music and nature sounds to create recordings that soothe, inspire, empower and heal. Her own life challenges of dealing with loss and illness as well as the joys of creative soul exploration inspire her work with clients and the writing of her meditations.
